var __index = {"config":{"separator":"[\\\\s\\\\-,:!=\\\\[\\\\]()\\\"`/]+|\\\\.(?!\\\\d)|&[lg]t;|(?!\\\\b)(?=[A-Z][a-z])"},"items":[{"location":"index.html","level":1,"title":"cspilot Documentation","text":"<p><code>cspilot</code> provides recorded computational chemistry workflows from structures, local executables, and optional AGAPI-backed tool selection.</p>","path":["cspilot Documentation"],"tags":[]},{"location":"index.html#start-here","level":2,"title":"Start Here","text":"<ul> <li>Installation</li> <li>Configuration</li> <li>CLI Usage</li> <li>Examples</li> </ul>","path":["cspilot Documentation"],"tags":[]},{"location":"index.html#operation","level":2,"title":"Operation","text":"<ul> <li>Agent Usage</li> <li>Workflows</li> <li>Tools</li> <li>AGAPI Integration</li> <li>Safety</li> </ul>","path":["cspilot Documentation"],"tags":[]},{"location":"index.html#project-maintenance","level":2,"title":"Project Maintenance","text":"<ul> <li>Development</li> <li>Roadmap</li> <li>Updating Documentation</li> </ul> <p>Features described as planned are not available commands or tools in the current package.</p>","path":["cspilot Documentation"],"tags":[]},{"location":"agapi.html","level":1,"title":"AGAPI Integration","text":"<p><code>cspilot</code> contains two related AGAPI integration paths.</p>","path":["Capabilities","AGAPI Integration"],"tags":[]},{"location":"agapi.html#openai-compatible-agent-backend","level":2,"title":"OpenAI-Compatible Agent Backend","text":"<p>The Agents SDK path constructs an asynchronous OpenAI-compatible client using:</p> <pre><code>AGAPI_API_KEY=your_api_key\nAGAPI_BASE_URL=https://atomgpt.org/api\ncspilot_MODEL=openai/gpt-oss-20b\n</code></pre> <p>It is used by <code>cspilot agent</code>, <code>cspilot plan</code>, and <code>cspilot run</code>. The model selects only the tools made available by the relevant agent or profile registry.</p> <p>The direct agent supports model/backend overrides:</p> <pre><code>cspilot agent \"inspect input.xyz\" --workdir runs/agent-check \\\n  --model openai/gpt-oss-20b --base-url https://atomgpt.org/api\n</code></pre>","path":["Capabilities","AGAPI Integration"],"tags":[]},{"location":"agapi.html#agapi-prebuilt-materials-query","level":2,"title":"AGAPI Prebuilt Materials Query","text":"<p>The optional <code>agapi_materials_query</code> wrapper imports the AGAPI prebuilt <code>AGAPIAgent</code> and delegates to:</p> <pre><code>agent.query_sync(query, render_html=render_html)\n</code></pre> <p>It is exposed through the planner/executor registry for the <code>materials</code> profile:</p> <pre><code>cspilot run \"Find all Al2O3 materials\" --workdir runs/al2o3 \\\n  --profile materials --html\n</code></pre> <p>The <code>--html</code> switch above controls cspilot's final execution report. <code>AGAPIAgent</code> may display its own rendered output in notebook environments; the cspilot result records the returned response content.</p>","path":["Capabilities","AGAPI Integration"],"tags":[]},{"location":"agapi.html#local-tools-versus-agapi-prebuilt-tools","level":2,"title":"Local Tools Versus AGAPI Prebuilt Tools","text":"Kind Examples Authority for returned data Local cspilot tool ASE inspection, xTB, ORCA/OPI, MACE, JSON parsing Local inputs and local executable output AGAPI prebuilt tool Materials/JARVIS-style natural-language query AGAPI service response <p>AGAPI is not used to fabricate local ORCA or xTB results. If a local calculation did not run or a parsed property is absent, reports must state that limitation.</p>","path":["Capabilities","AGAPI Integration"],"tags":[]},{"location":"agent_usage.html","level":1,"title":"Agent Usage","text":"","path":["Capabilities","Agent Usage"],"tags":[]},{"location":"agent_usage.html#deterministic-commands-versus-agent-mode","level":2,"title":"Deterministic Commands Versus Agent Mode","text":"<p>Use deterministic CLI commands when you know the operation and input file:</p> <pre><code>cspilot workflow xtb-orca-freq input.xyz --method r2scan-3c --basis def2-SVP\n</code></pre> <p>Use an agent command when the request needs interpretation, molecule input conversion, materials querying, or property retrieval:</p> <pre><code>cspilot agent \"gibbs free energy of water in ORCA r2scan-3c\" \\\n  --workdir runs/water-agent --agent-profile chem\n</code></pre> <p>The direct agent can select tools and write <code>agent_result.json</code>. It does not replace calculation programs or validate a scientific method choice.</p>","path":["Capabilities","Agent Usage"],"tags":[]},{"location":"agent_usage.html#planner-and-executor","level":2,"title":"Planner And Executor","text":"<p><code>plan</code>, <code>execute</code>, and <code>run</code> use a stricter JSON workflow:</p> <ol> <li>The planner requests a JSON list of registered tools and arguments from the    AGAPI model.</li> <li>The executor rejects names outside the selected profile allowlist.</li> <li>Each tool result is written as JSON.</li> <li><code>run</code> verifies returned paths and numeric property fields and writes a    report.</li> </ol> <pre><code>cspilot run \"Find all Al2O3 materials\" --workdir runs/al2o3 \\\n  --profile materials --html\n</code></pre> <p><code>--html</code> belongs to <code>run</code>; it writes <code>final_report.html</code>.</p>","path":["Capabilities","Agent Usage"],"tags":[]},{"location":"agent_usage.html#agapi-backend-selection","level":2,"title":"AGAPI Backend Selection","text":"<p>Agent and planning calls need:</p> <pre><code>AGAPI_API_KEY=your_api_key\nAGAPI_BASE_URL=https://atomgpt.org/api\ncspilot_MODEL=openai/gpt-oss-20b\n</code></pre> <p>The direct <code>agent</code> command can override model and base URL:</p> <pre><code>cspilot agent \"inspect input.xyz\" --workdir runs/check \\\n  --model openai/gpt-oss-20b --base-url https://atomgpt.org/api\n</code></pre>","path":["Capabilities","Agent Usage"],"tags":[]},{"location":"agent_usage.html#profiles","level":2,"title":"Profiles","text":"<p><code>agent --agent-profile</code> currently accepts:</p> Profile Purpose <code>chem</code> Chemistry calculation and molecular input tools <code>materials</code> Materials-oriented direct-agent instructions; currently exposes the same local calculation tools as <code>chem</code> <code>general</code> No registered direct-agent calculation tools <p><code>plan</code>, <code>execute</code>, and <code>run --profile</code> accept:</p> Profile Executor allowlist <code>chem</code> ASE/xTB/ORCA/MACE chemistry tools <code>materials</code> AGAPI materials-query wrapper <code>analysis</code> Result JSON search/property tools <code>thermo</code> Result JSON search/property tools <code>general</code> No calculation tools; materials query is permitted only when explicitly requested during <code>run</code> planning","path":["Capabilities","Agent Usage"],"tags":[]},{"location":"agent_usage.html#agent-rules","level":2,"title":"Agent Rules","text":"<p>The implemented prompts and executor are designed to enforce these rules:</p> <ul> <li>Use only provided or allowlisted tools.</li> <li>Never invent structures, energies, files, or property values.</li> <li>Prefer the fixed xTB to ORCA single-point workflow where applicable.</li> <li>Use the xTB to ORCA frequency workflow for a new Gibbs free-energy request   in direct chem agent mode.</li> <li>Search previous JSON output for requested existing properties.</li> <li>Report unsupported behavior or absent properties clearly.</li> </ul> <p>Agent results remain dependent on external executables, external API responses, and the quality of the chosen computational method.</p>","path":["Capabilities","Agent Usage"],"tags":[]},{"location":"cli_usage.html","level":1,"title":"CLI Usage","text":"<p>Commands below are defined in <code>src/cspilot/cli.py</code>. The installed script name is <code>cspilot</code>; a legacy <code>cspiolt</code> alias also currently exists.</p>","path":["Getting Started","CLI Usage"],"tags":[]},{"location":"cli_usage.html#deterministic-commands","level":2,"title":"Deterministic Commands","text":"","path":["Getting Started","CLI Usage"],"tags":[]},{"location":"cli_usage.html#inspect","level":3,"title":"<code>inspect</code>","text":"<p>Purpose: read an XYZ structure with ASE and print formula, atom count, periodicity, and center of mass.</p> <pre><code>cspilot inspect input.xyz\n</code></pre> <p>Output: <code>runs/&lt;timestamp&gt;-inspect/input.xyz</code> and <code>result.json</code>.</p>","path":["Getting Started","CLI Usage"],"tags":[]},{"location":"cli_usage.html#xtb-opt","level":3,"title":"<code>xtb-opt</code>","text":"<p>Purpose: optimize an XYZ geometry with xTB.</p> <pre><code>cspilot xtb-opt input.xyz --charge 0 --uhf 0\n</code></pre> <p>Output: <code>runs/&lt;timestamp&gt;-xtb-opt/result.json</code> and, after successful xTB execution, <code>xtbopt.xyz</code> and <code>xtbopt.log</code>.</p>","path":["Getting Started","CLI Usage"],"tags":[]},{"location":"cli_usage.html#orca-sp","level":3,"title":"<code>orca-sp</code>","text":"<p>Purpose: run an ORCA single-point calculation through OPI.</p> <pre><code>cspilot orca-sp input.xyz --method r2scan-3c --basis def2-SVP --charge 0 --mult 1\n</code></pre> <p>Output: <code>runs/&lt;timestamp&gt;-orca-sp/result.json</code>, OPI input <code>job.inp</code>, and successful ORCA output <code>job.out</code>.</p>","path":["Getting Started","CLI Usage"],"tags":[]},{"location":"cli_usage.html#mace-opt","level":3,"title":"<code>mace-opt</code>","text":"<p>Purpose: optimize geometry with an optional MACE calculator and model file.</p> <pre><code>cspilot mace-opt input.xyz --model /path/to/model.model\n</code></pre> <p>Output: <code>runs/&lt;timestamp&gt;-mace-opt/result.json</code>; on success, <code>mace_opt.xyz</code>, <code>mace_opt.traj</code>, and <code>mace_opt.log</code>.</p>","path":["Getting Started","CLI Usage"],"tags":[]},{"location":"cli_usage.html#fixed-workflows","level":2,"title":"Fixed Workflows","text":"","path":["Getting Started","CLI Usage"],"tags":[]},{"location":"cli_usage.html#workflow-xtb-orca-sp","level":3,"title":"<code>workflow xtb-orca-sp</code>","text":"<pre><code>cspilot workflow xtb-orca-sp input.xyz --charge 0 --mult 1 \\\n  --method r2scan-3c --basis def2-SVP\n</code></pre> <p>Output: <code>runs/&lt;timestamp&gt;-xtb-orca-sp/workflow_result.json</code>, plus <code>01_xtb_opt/</code> and <code>02_orca_sp/</code> job files when the steps run.</p>","path":["Getting Started","CLI Usage"],"tags":[]},{"location":"cli_usage.html#workflow-xtb-orca-freq","level":3,"title":"<code>workflow xtb-orca-freq</code>","text":"<pre><code>cspilot workflow xtb-orca-freq input.xyz --charge 0 --mult 1 \\\n  --method r2scan-3c --basis def2-SVP\n</code></pre> <p>Output: <code>runs/&lt;timestamp&gt;-xtb-orca-freq/workflow_result.json</code>, plus <code>01_xtb_opt/</code> and <code>02_orca_freq/</code> job files. Gibbs free energy is recorded only when parsed from the ORCA result.</p>","path":["Getting Started","CLI Usage"],"tags":[]},{"location":"cli_usage.html#workflow-mace-orca","level":3,"title":"<code>workflow mace-orca</code>","text":"<pre><code>cspilot workflow mace-orca input.xyz --model /path/to/model.model \\\n  --charge 0 --mult 1 --method r2scan-3c --basis def2-SVP\n</code></pre> <p>Output: <code>runs/&lt;timestamp&gt;-mace-orca/workflow_result.json</code>, plus MACE and ORCA subdirectories when executed successfully.</p>","path":["Getting Started","CLI Usage"],"tags":[]},{"location":"cli_usage.html#agapi-and-agent-commands","level":2,"title":"AGAPI And Agent Commands","text":"","path":["Getting Started","CLI Usage"],"tags":[]},{"location":"cli_usage.html#agent","level":3,"title":"<code>agent</code>","text":"<p>Purpose: let an AGAPI-backed Agents SDK agent select exposed tools directly. Supported direct-agent profiles are <code>chem</code>, <code>materials</code>, and <code>general</code>.</p> <pre><code>cspilot agent \"gibbs free energy of water in ORCA r2scan-3c\" \\\n  --workdir runs/water-agent --agent-profile chem\n</code></pre> <p>Options include <code>--model</code> and <code>--base-url</code>.</p> <p>Output: <code>&lt;workdir&gt;/agent_result.json</code> plus calculation subruns selected by the agent.</p>","path":["Getting Started","CLI Usage"],"tags":[]},{"location":"cli_usage.html#plan","level":3,"title":"<code>plan</code>","text":"<p>Purpose: produce a JSON plan without executing it. Planner profiles are <code>chem</code>, <code>materials</code>, <code>analysis</code>, <code>thermo</code>, and <code>general</code>.</p> <pre><code>cspilot plan \"Find all Al2O3 materials\" --workdir runs/al2o3 --profile materials\n</code></pre> <p>Output: <code>&lt;workdir&gt;/plan.json</code>.</p>","path":["Getting Started","CLI Usage"],"tags":[]},{"location":"cli_usage.html#execute","level":3,"title":"<code>execute</code>","text":"<p>Purpose: execute an existing JSON plan through the profile allowlist only.</p> <pre><code>cspilot execute runs/al2o3/plan.json --workdir runs/al2o3 --profile materials\n</code></pre> <p>Output: <code>&lt;workdir&gt;/plan.json</code>, <code>step_001_result.json</code> for each executed step, and <code>execution_result.json</code>.</p>","path":["Getting Started","CLI Usage"],"tags":[]},{"location":"cli_usage.html#run","level":3,"title":"<code>run</code>","text":"<p>Purpose: plan, execute, verify, and create a final deterministic report.</p> <pre><code>cspilot run \"Find all Al2O3 materials\" --workdir runs/al2o3 \\\n  --profile materials --html\n</code></pre> <p>Output: <code>&lt;workdir&gt;/plan.json</code>, step result JSON files, <code>execution_result.json</code>, <code>verification_result.json</code>, and either <code>final_report.md</code> or <code>final_report.html</code>.</p>","path":["Getting Started","CLI Usage"],"tags":[]},{"location":"configuration.html","level":1,"title":"Configuration","text":"<p><code>cspilot</code> loads <code>.env.cspilot</code> from the current working directory. Do not commit API keys or licensed-software configuration containing secrets.</p>","path":["Getting Started","Configuration"],"tags":[]},{"location":"configuration.html#implemented-variables","level":2,"title":"Implemented Variables","text":"<pre><code>CSPILOT_RUNS_DIR=runs\nXTB_COMMAND=xtb\nORCA_COMMAND=/path/to/orca\nMACE_MODEL=/path/to/mace_model.model\n\nAGAPI_API_KEY=your_api_key\nAGAPI_BASE_URL=https://atomgpt.org/api\ncspilot_MODEL=openai/gpt-oss-20b\n</code></pre> Variable Used by Default or requirement <code>CSPILOT_RUNS_DIR</code> Deterministic commands and workflows <code>runs</code> <code>XTB_COMMAND</code> xTB optimization <code>xtb</code> <code>ORCA_COMMAND</code> ORCA CLI and workflows <code>orca</code> <code>MACE_MODEL</code> <code>workflow mace-orca</code> when <code>--model</code> is omitted <code>model_path</code> placeholder <code>AGAPI_API_KEY</code> <code>agent</code>, <code>plan</code>, <code>run</code>, AGAPI materials wrapper Required for AGAPI calls <code>AGAPI_BASE_URL</code> OpenAI-compatible agent/planner client Required unless <code>--base-url</code> is supplied where supported <code>cspilot_MODEL</code> OpenAI-compatible agent/planner model Required unless <code>--model</code> is supplied for <code>agent</code> <p>The OPI integration also recognizes <code>OPI_ORCA</code> and <code>ORCA_PATH</code> when its Python API is invoked without an explicitly supplied ORCA command. The CLI uses <code>ORCA_COMMAND</code> through application settings.</p>","path":["Getting Started","Configuration"],"tags":[]},{"location":"configuration.html#names-not-currently-implemented","level":2,"title":"Names Not Currently Implemented","text":"<p>The following proposed variable names are not read by current source code:</p> Requested name Current status Use now <code>XTB_BIN</code> Not implemented <code>XTB_COMMAND</code> <code>ORCA_BIN</code> Not implemented <code>ORCA_COMMAND</code> <code>MULTIWFN_BIN</code> Planned with Multiwfn support None <code>MACE_MODEL_PATH</code> Not implemented <code>MACE_MODEL</code> or <code>--model</code>","path":["Getting Started","Configuration"],"tags":[]},{"location":"configuration.html#work-directories","level":2,"title":"Work Directories","text":"<ul> <li><code>inspect</code>, <code>xtb-opt</code>, <code>orca-sp</code>, <code>mace-opt</code>, and <code>workflow ...</code> use   <code>CSPILOT_RUNS_DIR</code> and create timestamped directories such as   <code>runs/20260527-170000-000000-orca-sp/</code>.</li> <li><code>agent</code>, <code>plan</code>, <code>execute</code>, and <code>run</code> accept an explicit <code>--workdir</code>.</li> <li>Default agent workdir: <code>runs/agent_test</code>.</li> <li>Default planner/executor/run workdir: <code>runs/test</code>.</li> </ul>","path":["Getting Started","Configuration"],"tags":[]},{"location":"development.html","level":1,"title":"Development","text":"","path":["Project","Development"],"tags":[]},{"location":"development.html#local-setup","level":2,"title":"Local Setup","text":"<pre><code>uv sync --extra dev\nuv run --extra dev pytest -q\nuv run --extra dev ruff check src tests\n</code></pre> <p>The package uses a <code>src/</code> layout; the Typer entry point is <code>cspilot.cli:app</code>.</p>","path":["Project","Development"],"tags":[]},{"location":"development.html#design-boundaries","level":2,"title":"Design Boundaries","text":"<ul> <li>Deterministic tools perform file and executable work.</li> <li>Workflows compose existing deterministic tools.</li> <li>Agent tools wrap implemented functions and return JSON-serializable data.</li> <li>The planner emits JSON tool plans; the executor runs only registered tools.</li> <li>The verifier and reporter inspect returned data without using an LLM to   create scientific values.</li> </ul>","path":["Project","Development"],"tags":[]},{"location":"development.html#adding-capabilities","level":2,"title":"Adding Capabilities","text":"<p>When adding a tool or workflow:</p> <ol> <li>Keep external execution in deterministic Python code.</li> <li>Return explicit status, paths, and parsed values.</li> <li>Add agent exposure only when the deterministic implementation is stable.</li> <li>Add tests for failure states and result serialization.</li> <li>Update documentation according to Updating Documentation.</li> </ol>","path":["Project","Development"],"tags":[]},{"location":"development.html#documentation","level":2,"title":"Documentation","text":"<p>Documentation dependencies are available through:</p> <pre><code>uv sync --extra docs\n</code></pre> <p>The user-facing pages in <code>docs/</code> should describe only implemented commands and mark roadmap work as planned.</p>","path":["Project","Development"],"tags":[]},{"location":"examples.html","level":1,"title":"Examples","text":"<p>The examples assume installation is complete and <code>.env.cspilot</code> contains paths for any external programs being used.</p>","path":["Getting Started","Examples"],"tags":[]},{"location":"examples.html#inspect-an-xyz-file","level":2,"title":"Inspect An XYZ File","text":"<pre><code>cspilot inspect tests/examples/input.xyz\n</code></pre> <p>Result: a structure table in the terminal and <code>runs/&lt;timestamp&gt;-inspect/result.json</code>.</p>","path":["Getting Started","Examples"],"tags":[]},{"location":"examples.html#generate-xyz-from-a-molecule-name","level":2,"title":"Generate XYZ From A Molecule Name","text":"<p>Molecule conversion is currently an agent tool rather than a standalone CLI subcommand:</p> <pre><code>cspilot agent \"Create an XYZ file for water at runs/water-agent/water.xyz\" \\\n  --workdir runs/water-agent --agent-profile chem\n</code></pre> <p>This requires AGAPI and PubChem access. For a deterministic Python call:</p> <pre><code>python -c \"from cspilot.tools.mol_tools import molecule_name_to_xyz; print(molecule_name_to_xyz('water', 'runs/water.xyz'))\"\n</code></pre>","path":["Getting Started","Examples"],"tags":[]},{"location":"examples.html#optimize-with-xtb","level":2,"title":"Optimize With xTB","text":"<pre><code>cspilot xtb-opt tests/examples/input.xyz --charge 0 --uhf 0\n</code></pre> <p>Result: <code>result.json</code> and, when xTB succeeds, <code>xtbopt.xyz</code>.</p>","path":["Getting Started","Examples"],"tags":[]},{"location":"examples.html#run-an-orca-single-point","level":2,"title":"Run An ORCA Single Point","text":"<pre><code>cspilot orca-sp tests/examples/input.xyz --method r2scan-3c \\\n  --basis def2-SVP --charge 0 --mult 1\n</code></pre> <p>Result: <code>result.json</code>, <code>job.inp</code>, and <code>job.out</code> after successful ORCA execution.</p>","path":["Getting Started","Examples"],"tags":[]},{"location":"examples.html#xtb-to-orca-workflow","level":2,"title":"xTB To ORCA Workflow","text":"<pre><code>cspilot workflow xtb-orca-sp tests/examples/input.xyz --charge 0 --mult 1 \\\n  --method r2scan-3c --basis def2-SVP\n</code></pre> <p>For a thermochemistry-capable frequency calculation:</p> <pre><code>cspilot workflow xtb-orca-freq tests/examples/input.xyz --charge 0 --mult 1 \\\n  --method r2scan-3c --basis def2-SVP\n</code></pre> <p>Result: <code>workflow_result.json</code>, with parsed properties only when present in successful ORCA output.</p>","path":["Getting Started","Examples"],"tags":[]},{"location":"examples.html#query-agapi-materials","level":2,"title":"Query AGAPI Materials","text":"<pre><code>cspilot run \"Find all Al2O3 materials\" --workdir runs/al2o3 \\\n  --profile materials --html\n</code></pre> <p>Result: plan, step and execution JSON files, verification JSON, and <code>runs/al2o3/final_report.html</code>.</p>","path":["Getting Started","Examples"],"tags":[]},{"location":"examples.html#extract-a-property-from-existing-json-results","level":2,"title":"Extract A Property From Existing JSON Results","text":"<p>Using the analysis planner/executor profile:</p> <pre><code>cspilot run \"Find the Gibbs free energy in runs/water-freq/workflow_result.json\" \\\n  --workdir runs/water-analysis --profile analysis\n</code></pre> <p>Or call the deterministic Python function directly:</p> <pre><code>python -c \"from cspilot.tools.result_tools import get_property_from_result; print(get_property_from_result('runs/water-freq/workflow_result.json', 'gibbs free energy'))\"\n</code></pre> <p>If Gibbs free energy was not present in the selected JSON, the result reports that it was not found.</p>","path":["Getting Started","Examples"],"tags":[]},{"location":"installation.html","level":1,"title":"Installation","text":"","path":["Getting Started","Installation"],"tags":[]},{"location":"installation.html#requirements","level":2,"title":"Requirements","text":"<ul> <li>Python 3.11 or newer.</li> <li>An XYZ input file for deterministic structure and calculation commands.</li> <li>xTB and/or ORCA executables installed separately for the corresponding jobs.</li> </ul>","path":["Getting Started","Installation"],"tags":[]},{"location":"installation.html#install-with-uv","level":2,"title":"Install With uv","text":"<p>From the repository root:</p> <pre><code>uv sync\nuv run cspilot --help\n</code></pre> <p>Install the optional MACE dependency set:</p> <pre><code>uv sync --extra mace\n</code></pre> <p>Development and documentation extras are also defined:</p> <pre><code>uv sync --extra dev\nuv sync --extra docs\n</code></pre>","path":["Getting Started","Installation"],"tags":[]},{"location":"installation.html#editable-pip-install","level":2,"title":"Editable pip Install","text":"<pre><code>python -m venv .venv\nsource .venv/bin/activate\npython -m pip install --upgrade pip\npython -m pip install -e .\n</code></pre> <p>For MACE:</p> <pre><code>python -m pip install -e \".[mace]\"\n</code></pre> <p>Optional groups in <code>pyproject.toml</code>:</p> Extra Purpose <code>dev</code> pytest, coverage, and Ruff <code>docs</code> documentation tooling <code>mace</code> <code>mace-torch</code> calculator support","path":["Getting Started","Installation"],"tags":[]},{"location":"installation.html#external-programs","level":2,"title":"External Programs","text":"Program Status Installation note xTB Used by <code>xtb-opt</code> and xTB workflows Install externally and configure <code>XTB_COMMAND</code>. ORCA Used by <code>orca-sp</code> and ORCA workflows Install separately under the ORCA license and configure <code>ORCA_COMMAND</code>. ORCA is not installed by pip. Multiwfn Planned, not currently called No cspilot configuration or CLI support yet. <p><code>orca-pi</code> supplies the Python interface and parsers; it is not the ORCA quantum chemistry executable.</p>","path":["Getting Started","Installation"],"tags":[]},{"location":"installation.html#sanity-check","level":2,"title":"Sanity Check","text":"<pre><code>uv run cspilot inspect tests/examples/input.xyz\n</code></pre> <p>This command only needs Python dependencies and should produce a timestamped <code>runs/*-inspect/result.json</code> record.</p>","path":["Getting Started","Installation"],"tags":[]},{"location":"roadmap.html","level":1,"title":"Roadmap","text":"<p>Implemented stages and planned work are separated explicitly below.</p> Stage Status Scope v0.1 Implemented Deterministic CLI for structure inspection and local calculations v0.2 Implemented Fixed xTB/MACE to ORCA workflows v0.3 Implemented AGAPI agent plus planner/executor v0.4 In progress Documentation and test coverage v0.5 Planned Multiwfn post-processing tools v0.6 Planned LangGraph retry/repair orchestration v0.7 Planned stk structure generation v0.8 Planned torch-sim MLIP molecular dynamics v0.9 Planned MongoDB job database v1.0 Planned MCP server v1.1 Planned Streamlit user interface <p>Planned entries are not current CLI commands, Python tools, or installation requirements.</p>","path":["Project","Roadmap"],"tags":[]},{"location":"safety.html","level":1,"title":"Safety And Scientific Integrity","text":"","path":["Capabilities","Safety And Scientific Integrity"],"tags":[]},{"location":"safety.html#implemented-controls","level":2,"title":"Implemented Controls","text":"<ul> <li>The JSON executor calls only tools in a fixed registry and selected profile   allowlist.</li> <li>Planner output is JSON data; it is never executed as shell commands.</li> <li>Agent instructions prohibit invented energies, structures, files, and   calculation results.</li> <li>Verification checks reported paths, ORCA/xTB expected output files, and   numeric energy-like values before reporting execution as verified.</li> <li>Result-query tools return \"Property not found\" when a value is absent.</li> <li>Local xTB and ORCA executable paths are selected through application   configuration in <code>.env.cspilot</code>, not generated by an LLM.</li> </ul>","path":["Capabilities","Safety And Scientific Integrity"],"tags":[]},{"location":"safety.html#external-software","level":2,"title":"External Software","text":"<p>Calculations execute third-party software on local input. Users remain responsible for:</p> <ul> <li>installing and licensing ORCA correctly;</li> <li>choosing methods, basis sets, charges, multiplicities, and models suitable   for the scientific question;</li> <li>reviewing raw output before relying on reported properties.</li> </ul>","path":["Capabilities","Safety And Scientific Integrity"],"tags":[]},{"location":"safety.html#planned-multiwfn-boundary","level":2,"title":"Planned Multiwfn Boundary","text":"<p>Multiwfn is not currently implemented. When it is added, only reviewed, whitelisted Multiwfn scripts or fixed operations should be exposed to an agent. Arbitrary LLM-generated Multiwfn or shell scripts must not be executed.</p>","path":["Capabilities","Safety And Scientific Integrity"],"tags":[]},{"location":"safety.html#secrets","level":2,"title":"Secrets","text":"<p>Keep <code>AGAPI_API_KEY</code> in <code>.env.cspilot</code> outside version control. Do not include credentials in reports, example inputs, or issue logs.</p>","path":["Capabilities","Safety And Scientific Integrity"],"tags":[]},{"location":"tools.html","level":1,"title":"Tools","text":"<p>This page describes implemented Python and agent tools. Not every Python function is a standalone CLI command.</p>","path":["Capabilities","Tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"tools.html#structure-tools","level":2,"title":"Structure Tools","text":"<p>Module: <code>cspilot.tools.ase_tools</code></p> Function Behavior <code>load_structure</code> Read a structure with ASE. <code>save_structure</code> Write a structure with ASE. <code>summarize_structure</code> Return formula, atom count, cell, PBC, and center of mass. <p>Agent wrapper: <code>inspect_structure</code>.</p>","path":["Capabilities","Tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"tools.html#molecule-conversion-tools","level":2,"title":"Molecule Conversion Tools","text":"<p>Module: <code>cspilot.tools.mol_tools</code></p> Function Behavior <code>molecule_name_to_smiles</code> Resolve a name using PubChem. <code>validate_smiles</code> Validate and canonicalize a SMILES string with RDKit. <code>canonicalize_smiles</code> Return canonical RDKit SMILES. <code>smiles_to_xyz</code> Embed conformers with ETKDGv3, minimize with MMFF or UFF, and write the lowest-energy XYZ conformer. <code>molecule_name_to_xyz</code> Combine PubChem lookup and RDKit XYZ generation. <p>These are exposed to the direct agent as tools; there are currently no standalone molecule-conversion CLI subcommands.</p>","path":["Capabilities","Tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"tools.html#xtb-tools","level":2,"title":"xTB Tools","text":"<p>Module: <code>cspilot.tools.xtb_tools</code></p> Function Behavior <code>optimize_with_xtb</code> Execute <code>XTB_COMMAND &lt;input&gt; --opt --chrg ... --uhf ...</code> and return expected optimization paths. <p>CLI: <code>xtb-opt</code>. Agent wrapper: <code>run_xtb_optimize</code>.</p> <p>xTB single-point calculation is not currently implemented.</p>","path":["Capabilities","Tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"tools.html#orca-and-opi-tools","level":2,"title":"ORCA And OPI Tools","text":"<p>Module: <code>cspilot.tools.opi_orca_tools</code></p> Function Behavior <code>orca_single_point</code> Create and execute an OPI ORCA SP job. <code>orca_optimize</code> Create and execute an OPI ORCA optimization job. <code>orca_frequency</code> Create and execute an OPI ORCA frequency job. <code>parse_orca_result</code> Parse with OPI where possible and fill missing supported values from ORCA text. <code>single_point_with_orca</code> Adapter used by <code>orca-sp</code>. <p>The parser can report returned final energy, orbital-gap data, dipole, zero-point energy, Gibbs free energy, enthalpy, entropy, and IR data when available in successful output. It does not synthesize missing properties.</p>","path":["Capabilities","Tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"tools.html#mace-tools","level":2,"title":"MACE Tools","text":"<p>Module: <code>cspilot.tools.mace_tools</code></p> <p><code>optimize_with_mace</code> runs ASE BFGS with <code>MACECalculator</code>, writes an optimized XYZ, trajectory, and log, and returns the MACE energy when successful. It requires <code>mace-torch</code> and a model file.</p> <p>CLI: <code>mace-opt</code>. Agent wrapper: <code>run_mace_optimize</code>.</p>","path":["Capabilities","Tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"tools.html#agapi-materials-tools","level":2,"title":"AGAPI Materials Tools","text":"<p>Module: <code>cspilot.tools.agapi_materials_tools</code></p> <p><code>agapi_materials_query</code> optionally imports <code>AGAPIAgent</code> and delegates a natural-language materials query through its prebuilt <code>query_sync</code> function. It is available to planner/executor workflows in the <code>materials</code> profile and for explicit materials requests in the <code>general</code> run profile.</p>","path":["Capabilities","Tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"tools.html#result-json-tools","level":2,"title":"Result JSON Tools","text":"<p>Module: <code>cspilot.tools.result_tools</code></p> Function Behavior <code>find_result_json</code> Recursively find supported run JSON records. <code>load_result_json</code> Load JSON from a supplied path. <code>get_property_from_result</code> Search nested results using supported aliases. <p>Supported query aliases include Gibbs free energy, enthalpy, electronic/final energy, HOMO-LUMO gap, and frequencies. Failure to find a property returns an explicit error rather than a guessed value.</p>","path":["Capabilities","Tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"updating_docs.html","level":1,"title":"Updating Documentation","text":"<p>Documentation is part of a user-facing change. Every time a function, tool, workflow, command, or configurable integration is added or changed:</p> <ul> <li>Update <code>README.md</code> when the capability is user-facing.</li> <li>Update <code>docs/tools.md</code> for each new or changed tool.</li> <li>Update <code>docs/workflows.md</code> for each new or changed workflow.</li> <li>Update <code>docs/cli_usage.md</code> for each new or changed CLI command or option.</li> <li>Update <code>docs/configuration.md</code> for each new or changed environment variable.</li> <li>Update <code>docs/examples.md</code> when a new use case becomes possible.</li> <li>Add or update tests that establish the documented behavior.</li> <li>Add a changelog entry when <code>CHANGELOG.md</code> exists.</li> </ul>","path":["Project","Updating Documentation"],"tags":[]},{"location":"updating_docs.html#accuracy-rules","level":2,"title":"Accuracy Rules","text":"<ul> <li>Read implementation code before documenting an interface.</li> <li>Do not publish commands, environment variables, files, or outputs that are   not implemented.</li> <li>Clearly label roadmap work as planned.</li> <li>Never place real API keys, licensed-software data, or private paths in   documentation examples.</li> </ul>","path":["Project","Updating Documentation"],"tags":[]},{"location":"workflows.html","level":1,"title":"Workflows","text":"<p>All fixed workflows accept an XYZ input, copy it into a new timestamped run directory under <code>CSPILOT_RUNS_DIR</code>, execute sequential steps, and write <code>workflow_result.json</code>.</p>","path":["Capabilities","Workflows"],"tags":[]},{"location":"workflows.html#xtb-optimization-to-orca-single-point","level":2,"title":"xTB Optimization To ORCA Single Point","text":"<pre><code>cspilot workflow xtb-orca-sp input.xyz --charge 0 --mult 1 \\\n  --method r2scan-3c --basis def2-SVP --uhf 0 --nprocs 1\n</code></pre> <p>Steps:</p> <ol> <li>Copy <code>input.xyz</code>.</li> <li>Optimize geometry using xTB in <code>01_xtb_opt/</code>.</li> <li>If <code>xtbopt.xyz</code> exists after a successful optimization, run ORCA SP with    OPI in <code>02_orca_sp/</code>.</li> <li>Store parsed final energy when available.</li> </ol>","path":["Capabilities","Workflows"],"tags":[]},{"location":"workflows.html#xtb-optimization-to-orca-frequency","level":2,"title":"xTB Optimization To ORCA Frequency","text":"<pre><code>cspilot workflow xtb-orca-freq input.xyz --charge 0 --mult 1 \\\n  --method r2scan-3c --basis def2-SVP --uhf 0 --nprocs 1\n</code></pre> <p>Steps are the same as above, except step 3 invokes an ORCA frequency job in <code>02_orca_freq/</code>. OPI or the fallback text parser may store <code>gibbs_free_energy</code>, <code>enthalpy</code>, or zero-point energy if those values occur in the completed ORCA output.</p>","path":["Capabilities","Workflows"],"tags":[]},{"location":"workflows.html#mace-optimization-to-orca-single-point","level":2,"title":"MACE Optimization To ORCA Single Point","text":"<pre><code>cspilot workflow mace-orca input.xyz --model /path/to/model.model \\\n  --charge 0 --mult 1 --method r2scan-3c --basis def2-SVP\n</code></pre> <p>Steps:</p> <ol> <li>Copy <code>input.xyz</code>.</li> <li>Optimize geometry with MACE in <code>01_mace_opt/</code>.</li> <li>If MACE succeeds and creates <code>mace_opt.xyz</code>, run ORCA SP in <code>02_orca_sp/</code>.</li> </ol> <p>MACE requires the <code>mace</code> optional dependency and a valid local model. If <code>--model</code> is absent, this workflow reads <code>MACE_MODEL</code>.</p>","path":["Capabilities","Workflows"],"tags":[]},{"location":"workflows.html#result-json-shape","level":2,"title":"Result JSON Shape","text":"<p>The workflow result is a JSON object of the following form; property keys are present only when returned by tools:</p> <pre><code>{\n  \"workflow\": \"xtb-orca-freq\",\n  \"status\": \"ok\",\n  \"input_xyz\": \"/absolute/path/input.xyz\",\n  \"workdir\": \"runs/&lt;timestamp&gt;-xtb-orca-freq\",\n  \"steps\": {\n    \"xtb_opt\": {\n      \"status\": \"ok\",\n      \"outputs\": {\n        \"optimized_xyz\": \"runs/.../01_xtb_opt/xtbopt.xyz\"\n      }\n    },\n    \"orca_freq\": {\n      \"status\": \"ok\",\n      \"task\": \"freq\",\n      \"result\": {\n        \"properties\": {\n          \"final_energy_hartree\": -1.0,\n          \"gibbs_free_energy\": -1.0\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  },\n  \"final_energy_hartree\": -1.0,\n  \"workflow_result_path\": \"runs/.../workflow_result.json\"\n}\n</code></pre> <p>The numbers above show structure only and are not expected calculation values.</p>","path":["Capabilities","Workflows"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/SUMMARY.html","level":1,"title":"SUMMARY","text":"<ul> <li>cspilot<ul> <li>agents<ul> <li>executor</li> <li>openai_agent</li> <li>planner</li> <li>reporter</li> <li>verifier</li> </ul> </li> <li>cli</li> <li>config</li> <li>llm</li> <li>prompts<ul> <li>system_prompts</li> </ul> </li> <li>schemas</li> <li>tools<ul> <li>agapi_materials_tools</li> <li>agent_tools</li> <li>ase_tools</li> <li>mace_tools</li> <li>mol_tools</li> <li>opi_orca_tools</li> <li>registry</li> <li>result_tools</li> <li>xtb_tools</li> </ul> </li> <li>utils<ul> <li>runner</li> </ul> </li> <li>workflows<ul> <li>_common</li> <li>mace_to_orca</li> <li>xtb_to_orca_freq</li> <li>xtb_to_orca_sp</li> </ul> </li> </ul> </li> </ul>","path":["SUMMARY"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/cli.html","level":1,"title":"Cli","text":"","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Cli"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/cli.html#cspilot.cli.InputPath","level":2,"title":"InputPath  <code>module-attribute</code>","text":"<pre><code>InputPath = Annotated[Path, Argument(exists=True, file_okay=True, dir_okay=False, readable=True, resolve_path=True)]\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Cli"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/cli.html#cspilot.cli.Profile","level":2,"title":"Profile  <code>module-attribute</code>","text":"<pre><code>Profile = Literal['chem', 'materials', 'analysis', 'thermo', 'general']\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Cli"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/cli.html#cspilot.cli.app","level":2,"title":"app  <code>module-attribute</code>","text":"<pre><code>app = Typer(help='Computational chemistry workflow CLI.')\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Cli"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/cli.html#cspilot.cli.console","level":2,"title":"console  <code>module-attribute</code>","text":"<pre><code>console = Console()\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Cli"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/cli.html#cspilot.cli.workflow_app","level":2,"title":"workflow_app  <code>module-attribute</code>","text":"<pre><code>workflow_app = Typer(help='Multi-step computational chemistry workflows.')\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Cli"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/cli.html#cspilot.cli.execute_command","level":2,"title":"execute_command","text":"<pre><code>execute_command(plan_path: Annotated[Path, Argument(exists=True, file_okay=True, dir_okay=False, readable=True, resolve_path=True)], workdir: Annotated[Path, Option(help='Directory in which to save execution outputs.', resolve_path=True)] = Path('runs/test'), profile: Annotated[Profile, Option(help='Tool allowlist profile.')] = 'chem') -&gt; None\n</code></pre> <p>Execute an existing JSON plan through allowlisted local tools.</p> Source code in <code>cspilot/cli.py</code> <pre><code>@app.command(\"execute\")\ndef execute_command(\n    plan_path: Annotated[\n        Path,\n        typer.Argument(exists=True, file_okay=True, dir_okay=False, readable=True, resolve_path=True),\n    ],\n    workdir: Annotated[\n        Path,\n        typer.Option(help=\"Directory in which to save execution outputs.\", resolve_path=True),\n    ] = Path(\"runs/test\"),\n    profile: Annotated[Profile, typer.Option(help=\"Tool allowlist profile.\")] = \"chem\",\n) -&gt; None:\n    \"\"\"Execute an existing JSON plan through allowlisted local tools.\"\"\"\n    from cspilot.agents.executor import execute_plan\n    from cspilot.tools.registry import reset_allowed_profile, set_allowed_profile\n\n    workdir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n    profile_token = set_allowed_profile(profile)\n    try:\n        plan = json.loads(plan_path.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\"))\n        execution_result = execute_plan(plan, str(workdir))\n    except (OSError, json.JSONDecodeError, ValueError) as exc:\n        console.print(f\"[red]Execution error:[/] {exc}\")\n        raise typer.Exit(code=1) from exc\n    finally:\n        reset_allowed_profile(profile_token)\n    result_path = workdir / \"execution_result.json\"\n    _write_cli_json(result_path, execution_result)\n    _print_execution_summary(execution_result, result_path)\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Cli"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/cli.html#cspilot.cli.inspect","level":2,"title":"inspect","text":"<pre><code>inspect(input_path: InputPath) -&gt; None\n</code></pre> <p>Inspect a structure file with ASE.</p> Source code in <code>cspilot/cli.py</code> <pre><code>@app.command()\ndef inspect(input_path: InputPath) -&gt; None:\n    \"\"\"Inspect a structure file with ASE.\"\"\"\n    settings = load_settings()\n    run_dir = make_run_dir(settings.runs_dir, \"inspect\")\n    run_input = copy_input(input_path, run_dir)\n    summary = summarize_structure(run_input)\n\n    table = Table(title=\"Structure\")\n    table.add_column(\"Property\")\n    table.add_column(\"Value\")\n    table.add_row(\"Formula\", summary.formula)\n    table.add_row(\"Atoms\", str(summary.natoms))\n    table.add_row(\"PBC\", str(summary.pbc))\n    table.add_row(\"Center of mass\", \", \".join(f\"{value:.6f}\" for value in summary.center_of_mass))\n    console.print(table)\n\n    _finish(\n        CommandResult(\n            command=\"inspect\",\n            status=\"ok\",\n            run_dir=run_dir,\n            input_path=input_path,\n            structure=summary,\n            outputs={\"result_json\": str(run_dir / \"result.json\")},\n        )\n    )\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Cli"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/cli.html#cspilot.cli.mace_opt","level":2,"title":"mace_opt","text":"<pre><code>mace_opt(input_path: InputPath, model: Annotated[Path, Option(help='Path to a MACE model file.', resolve_path=True)], fmax: Annotated[float, Option(help='Force convergence threshold in eV/A.')] = 0.05, steps: Annotated[int, Option(help='Maximum optimizer steps.')] = 200) -&gt; None\n</code></pre> <p>Run a MACE geometry optimization.</p> Source code in <code>cspilot/cli.py</code> <pre><code>@app.command(\"mace-opt\")\ndef mace_opt(\n    input_path: InputPath,\n    model: Annotated[Path, typer.Option(help=\"Path to a MACE model file.\", resolve_path=True)],\n    fmax: Annotated[float, typer.Option(help=\"Force convergence threshold in eV/A.\")] = 0.05,\n    steps: Annotated[int, typer.Option(help=\"Maximum optimizer steps.\")] = 200,\n) -&gt; None:\n    \"\"\"Run a MACE geometry optimization.\"\"\"\n    settings = load_settings()\n    run_dir = make_run_dir(settings.runs_dir, \"mace-opt\")\n    run_input = copy_input(input_path, run_dir)\n    summary = summarize_structure(run_input)\n    ok, message, outputs = optimize_with_mace(run_input, run_dir, model, fmax=fmax, steps=steps)\n\n    _finish(\n        CommandResult(\n            command=\"mace-opt\",\n            status=\"ok\" if ok else \"skipped\",\n            run_dir=run_dir,\n            input_path=input_path,\n            structure=summary,\n            parameters={\"model\": str(model), \"fmax\": fmax, \"steps\": steps},\n            outputs=outputs,\n            message=message,\n        )\n    )\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Cli"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/cli.html#cspilot.cli.orca_sp","level":2,"title":"orca_sp","text":"<pre><code>orca_sp(input_path: InputPath, method: Annotated[str, Option(help='ORCA method keyword.')] = 'r2scan-3c', basis: Annotated[str, Option(help='ORCA basis keyword.')] = 'def2-SVP', charge: Annotated[int, Option(help='Molecular charge.')] = 0, mult: Annotated[int, Option(help='Spin multiplicity.')] = 1) -&gt; None\n</code></pre> <p>Run an ORCA single point calculation.</p> Source code in <code>cspilot/cli.py</code> <pre><code>@app.command(\"orca-sp\")\ndef orca_sp(\n    input_path: InputPath,\n    method: Annotated[str, typer.Option(help=\"ORCA method keyword.\")] = \"r2scan-3c\",\n    basis: Annotated[str, typer.Option(help=\"ORCA basis keyword.\")] = \"def2-SVP\",\n    charge: Annotated[int, typer.Option(help=\"Molecular charge.\")] = 0,\n    mult: Annotated[int, typer.Option(help=\"Spin multiplicity.\")] = 1,\n) -&gt; None:\n    \"\"\"Run an ORCA single point calculation.\"\"\"\n    settings = load_settings()\n    run_dir = make_run_dir(settings.runs_dir, \"orca-sp\")\n    run_input = copy_input(input_path, run_dir)\n    summary = summarize_structure(run_input)\n    ok, message, process, outputs = single_point_with_orca(\n        run_input,\n        run_dir,\n        settings,\n        method,\n        basis,\n        charge,\n        mult,\n    )\n\n    payload_outputs = dict(outputs)\n    if process is not None:\n        payload_outputs[\"process\"] = process.model_dump(mode=\"json\")\n\n    _finish(\n        CommandResult(\n            command=\"orca-sp\",\n            status=\"ok\" if ok else (\"failed\" if process is not None else \"skipped\"),\n            run_dir=run_dir,\n            input_path=input_path,\n            structure=summary,\n            parameters={\"method\": method, \"basis\": basis, \"charge\": charge, \"mult\": mult},\n            outputs=payload_outputs,\n            message=message,\n        )\n    )\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Cli"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/cli.html#cspilot.cli.plan_command","level":2,"title":"plan_command","text":"<pre><code>plan_command(request: Annotated[str, Argument(help='Natural language workflow request.')], workdir: Annotated[Path, Option(help='Directory in which to save plan.json.', resolve_path=True)] = Path('runs/test'), profile: Annotated[Profile, Option(help='Planning tool and prompt profile.')] = 'chem') -&gt; None\n</code></pre> <p>Create a JSON execution plan using the configured AGAPI planner.</p> Source code in <code>cspilot/cli.py</code> <pre><code>@app.command(\"plan\")\ndef plan_command(\n    request: Annotated[str, typer.Argument(help=\"Natural language workflow request.\")],\n    workdir: Annotated[\n        Path,\n        typer.Option(help=\"Directory in which to save plan.json.\", resolve_path=True),\n    ] = Path(\"runs/test\"),\n    profile: Annotated[Profile, typer.Option(help=\"Planning tool and prompt profile.\")] = \"chem\",\n) -&gt; None:\n    \"\"\"Create a JSON execution plan using the configured AGAPI planner.\"\"\"\n    from cspilot.agents.planner import create_plan\n\n    workdir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n    try:\n        plan = asyncio.run(create_plan(request, profile=profile))\n    except ValueError as exc:\n        console.print(f\"[red]Planning error:[/] {exc}\")\n        raise typer.Exit(code=1) from exc\n    plan_path = workdir / \"plan.json\"\n    _write_cli_json(plan_path, plan)\n    console.print_json(json=json.dumps(plan))\n    console.print(f\"Plan: {plan_path}\")\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Cli"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/cli.html#cspilot.cli.run_agent","level":2,"title":"run_agent","text":"<pre><code>run_agent(request: Annotated[str, Argument(help='Natural language computational chemistry request.')], workdir: Annotated[Path, Option(help='Directory for agent results and tool subruns.', resolve_path=True)] = Path('runs/agent_test'), model: Annotated[str | None, Option(help='AGAPI model identifier.')] = None, base_url: Annotated[str | None, Option(help='OpenAI-compatible AGAPI base URL.')] = None, agent_profile: Annotated[Literal['chem', 'materials', 'general'], Option(help='Agent instruction and tool profile.')] = 'chem') -&gt; None\n</code></pre> <p>Run a tool-using computational chemistry agent through AGAPI.</p> Source code in <code>cspilot/cli.py</code> <pre><code>@app.command(\"agent\")\ndef run_agent(\n    request: Annotated[str, typer.Argument(help=\"Natural language computational chemistry request.\")],\n    workdir: Annotated[\n        Path,\n        typer.Option(help=\"Directory for agent results and tool subruns.\", resolve_path=True),\n    ] = Path(\"runs/agent_test\"),\n    model: Annotated[str | None, typer.Option(help=\"AGAPI model identifier.\")] = None,\n    base_url: Annotated[str | None, typer.Option(help=\"OpenAI-compatible AGAPI base URL.\")] = None,\n    agent_profile: Annotated[\n        Literal[\"chem\", \"materials\", \"general\"],\n        typer.Option(help=\"Agent instruction and tool profile.\"),\n    ] = \"chem\",\n) -&gt; None:\n    \"\"\"Run a tool-using computational chemistry agent through AGAPI.\"\"\"\n    from cspilot.agents.openai_agent import run_agent_request\n\n    try:\n        result = asyncio.run(\n            run_agent_request(\n                request,\n                workdir,\n                model=model,\n                base_url=base_url,\n                profile=agent_profile,\n            )\n        )\n    except ValueError as exc:\n        console.print(f\"[red]Configuration error:[/] {exc}\")\n        raise typer.Exit(code=1) from exc\n    console.print(result[\"final_output\"])\n    console.print(f\"Result: {result['result_path']}\")\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Cli"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/cli.html#cspilot.cli.run_command","level":2,"title":"run_command","text":"<pre><code>run_command(request: Annotated[str, Argument(help='Natural language workflow request.')], workdir: Annotated[Path, Option(help='Directory in which to save plan and execution outputs.', resolve_path=True)] = Path('runs/test'), profile: Annotated[Profile, Option(help='Planning tool and report profile.')] = 'chem', html: Annotated[bool, Option(help='Write final_report.html instead of Markdown.')] = False) -&gt; None\n</code></pre> <p>Plan, execute, verify, and report an allowlisted workflow.</p> Source code in <code>cspilot/cli.py</code> <pre><code>@app.command(\"run\")\ndef run_command(\n    request: Annotated[str, typer.Argument(help=\"Natural language workflow request.\")],\n    workdir: Annotated[\n        Path,\n        typer.Option(help=\"Directory in which to save plan and execution outputs.\", resolve_path=True),\n    ] = Path(\"runs/test\"),\n    profile: Annotated[Profile, typer.Option(help=\"Planning tool and report profile.\")] = \"chem\",\n    html: Annotated[bool, typer.Option(help=\"Write final_report.html instead of Markdown.\")] = False,\n) -&gt; None:\n    \"\"\"Plan, execute, verify, and report an allowlisted workflow.\"\"\"\n    from cspilot.agents.executor import execute_plan\n    from cspilot.agents.planner import create_plan\n    from cspilot.agents.reporter import generate_report\n    from cspilot.agents.verifier import verify_execution\n    from cspilot.tools.registry import reset_allowed_profile, set_allowed_profile\n\n    workdir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n    profile_token = set_allowed_profile(profile, request)\n    try:\n        plan = asyncio.run(create_plan(request, profile=profile))\n        _write_cli_json(workdir / \"plan.json\", plan)\n        execution_result = execute_plan(plan, str(workdir))\n        _write_cli_json(workdir / \"execution_result.json\", execution_result)\n        verification_result = verify_execution(execution_result, str(workdir))\n        _write_cli_json(workdir / \"verification_result.json\", verification_result)\n        report = generate_report(\n            request,\n            plan,\n            execution_result,\n            verification_result,\n            html=html,\n            profile=profile,\n        )\n    except (OSError, ValueError) as exc:\n        console.print(f\"[red]Run error:[/] {exc}\")\n        raise typer.Exit(code=1) from exc\n    finally:\n        reset_allowed_profile(profile_token)\n\n    report_path = workdir / (\"final_report.html\" if html else \"final_report.md\")\n    report_path.write_text(report, encoding=\"utf-8\")\n    _print_execution_summary(execution_result, workdir / \"execution_result.json\")\n    status = \"PASSED\" if verification_result[\"verified\"] else \"FAILED\"\n    style = \"green\" if verification_result[\"verified\"] else \"red\"\n    console.print(f\"Verification: [{style}]{status}[/]\")\n    console.print(f\"Report: {report_path}\")\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Cli"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/cli.html#cspilot.cli.workflow_mace_orca","level":2,"title":"workflow_mace_orca","text":"<pre><code>workflow_mace_orca(input_path: InputPath, charge: Annotated[int, Option(help='Molecular charge.')] = 0, mult: Annotated[int, Option(help='Spin multiplicity.')] = 1, method: Annotated[str, Option(help='ORCA method keyword.')] = 'r2scan-3c', basis: Annotated[str, Option(help='ORCA basis keyword.')] = 'def2-SVP', model: Annotated[Path | None, Option(help='Path to a MACE model file. Defaults to MACE_MODEL or model_path.')] = None, fmax: Annotated[float, Option(help='MACE force convergence threshold in eV/A.')] = 0.05, steps: Annotated[int, Option(help='Maximum MACE optimizer steps.')] = 200, nprocs: Annotated[int, Option(help='ORCA processor count.')] = 1) -&gt; None\n</code></pre> <p>Run MACE optimization followed by an ORCA single point.</p> Source code in <code>cspilot/cli.py</code> <pre><code>@workflow_app.command(\"mace-orca\")\ndef workflow_mace_orca(\n    input_path: InputPath,\n    charge: Annotated[int, typer.Option(help=\"Molecular charge.\")] = 0,\n    mult: Annotated[int, typer.Option(help=\"Spin multiplicity.\")] = 1,\n    method: Annotated[str, typer.Option(help=\"ORCA method keyword.\")] = \"r2scan-3c\",\n    basis: Annotated[str, typer.Option(help=\"ORCA basis keyword.\")] = \"def2-SVP\",\n    model: Annotated[\n        Path | None,\n        typer.Option(help=\"Path to a MACE model file. Defaults to MACE_MODEL or model_path.\"),\n    ] = None,\n    fmax: Annotated[float, typer.Option(help=\"MACE force convergence threshold in eV/A.\")] = 0.05,\n    steps: Annotated[int, typer.Option(help=\"Maximum MACE optimizer steps.\")] = 200,\n    nprocs: Annotated[int, typer.Option(help=\"ORCA processor count.\")] = 1,\n) -&gt; None:\n    \"\"\"Run MACE optimization followed by an ORCA single point.\"\"\"\n    _finish_workflow(\n        run_mace_to_orca(\n            input_path,\n            charge=charge,\n            mult=mult,\n            method=method,\n            basis=basis,\n            model=model,\n            fmax=fmax,\n            steps=steps,\n            nprocs=nprocs,\n        )\n    )\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Cli"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/cli.html#cspilot.cli.workflow_xtb_orca_freq","level":2,"title":"workflow_xtb_orca_freq","text":"<pre><code>workflow_xtb_orca_freq(input_path: InputPath, charge: Annotated[int, Option(help='Molecular charge.')] = 0, mult: Annotated[int, Option(help='Spin multiplicity.')] = 1, method: Annotated[str, Option(help='ORCA method keyword.')] = 'r2scan-3c', basis: Annotated[str, Option(help='ORCA basis keyword.')] = 'def2-SVP', uhf: Annotated[int, Option(help='Number of unpaired electrons for xTB.')] = 0, nprocs: Annotated[int, Option(help='ORCA processor count.')] = 1) -&gt; None\n</code></pre> <p>Run xTB optimization followed by an ORCA frequency calculation.</p> Source code in <code>cspilot/cli.py</code> <pre><code>@workflow_app.command(\"xtb-orca-freq\")\ndef workflow_xtb_orca_freq(\n    input_path: InputPath,\n    charge: Annotated[int, typer.Option(help=\"Molecular charge.\")] = 0,\n    mult: Annotated[int, typer.Option(help=\"Spin multiplicity.\")] = 1,\n    method: Annotated[str, typer.Option(help=\"ORCA method keyword.\")] = \"r2scan-3c\",\n    basis: Annotated[str, typer.Option(help=\"ORCA basis keyword.\")] = \"def2-SVP\",\n    uhf: Annotated[int, typer.Option(help=\"Number of unpaired electrons for xTB.\")] = 0,\n    nprocs: Annotated[int, typer.Option(help=\"ORCA processor count.\")] = 1,\n) -&gt; None:\n    \"\"\"Run xTB optimization followed by an ORCA frequency calculation.\"\"\"\n    _finish_workflow(\n        run_xtb_to_orca_freq(\n            input_path,\n            charge=charge,\n            mult=mult,\n            method=method,\n            basis=basis,\n            uhf=uhf,\n            nprocs=nprocs,\n        )\n    )\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Cli"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/cli.html#cspilot.cli.workflow_xtb_orca_sp","level":2,"title":"workflow_xtb_orca_sp","text":"<pre><code>workflow_xtb_orca_sp(input_path: InputPath, charge: Annotated[int, Option(help='Molecular charge.')] = 0, mult: Annotated[int, Option(help='Spin multiplicity.')] = 1, method: Annotated[str, Option(help='ORCA method keyword.')] = 'r2scan-3c', basis: Annotated[str, Option(help='ORCA basis keyword.')] = 'def2-SVP', uhf: Annotated[int, Option(help='Number of unpaired electrons for xTB.')] = 0, nprocs: Annotated[int, Option(help='ORCA processor count.')] = 1) -&gt; None\n</code></pre> <p>Run xTB optimization followed by an ORCA single point.</p> Source code in <code>cspilot/cli.py</code> <pre><code>@workflow_app.command(\"xtb-orca-sp\")\ndef workflow_xtb_orca_sp(\n    input_path: InputPath,\n    charge: Annotated[int, typer.Option(help=\"Molecular charge.\")] = 0,\n    mult: Annotated[int, typer.Option(help=\"Spin multiplicity.\")] = 1,\n    method: Annotated[str, typer.Option(help=\"ORCA method keyword.\")] = \"r2scan-3c\",\n    basis: Annotated[str, typer.Option(help=\"ORCA basis keyword.\")] = \"def2-SVP\",\n    uhf: Annotated[int, typer.Option(help=\"Number of unpaired electrons for xTB.\")] = 0,\n    nprocs: Annotated[int, typer.Option(help=\"ORCA processor count.\")] = 1,\n) -&gt; None:\n    \"\"\"Run xTB optimization followed by an ORCA single point.\"\"\"\n    _finish_workflow(\n        run_xtb_to_orca_sp(\n            input_path,\n            charge=charge,\n            mult=mult,\n            method=method,\n            basis=basis,\n            uhf=uhf,\n            nprocs=nprocs,\n        )\n    )\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Cli"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/cli.html#cspilot.cli.xtb_opt","level":2,"title":"xtb_opt","text":"<pre><code>xtb_opt(input_path: InputPath, charge: Annotated[int, Option(help='Molecular charge.')] = 0, uhf: Annotated[int, Option(help='Number of unpaired electrons for xTB.')] = 0) -&gt; None\n</code></pre> <p>Run an xTB geometry optimization.</p> Source code in <code>cspilot/cli.py</code> <pre><code>@app.command(\"xtb-opt\")\ndef xtb_opt(\n    input_path: InputPath,\n    charge: Annotated[int, typer.Option(help=\"Molecular charge.\")] = 0,\n    uhf: Annotated[int, typer.Option(help=\"Number of unpaired electrons for xTB.\")] = 0,\n) -&gt; None:\n    \"\"\"Run an xTB geometry optimization.\"\"\"\n    settings = load_settings()\n    run_dir = make_run_dir(settings.runs_dir, \"xtb-opt\")\n    run_input = copy_input(input_path, run_dir)\n    summary = summarize_structure(run_input)\n    ok, message, process, outputs = optimize_with_xtb(run_input, run_dir, settings, charge, uhf)\n\n    payload_outputs = dict(outputs)\n    if process is not None:\n        payload_outputs[\"process\"] = process.model_dump(mode=\"json\")\n\n    _finish(\n        CommandResult(\n            command=\"xtb-opt\",\n            status=\"ok\" if ok else (\"failed\" if process is not None else \"skipped\"),\n            run_dir=run_dir,\n            input_path=input_path,\n            structure=summary,\n            parameters={\"charge\": charge, \"uhf\": uhf},\n            outputs=payload_outputs,\n            message=message,\n        )\n    )\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Cli"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/config.html","level":1,"title":"Config","text":"","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Config"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/config.html#cspilot.config.Settings","level":2,"title":"Settings","text":"<p>               Bases: <code>BaseModel</code></p>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Config"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/config.html#cspilot.config.Settings.orca_command","level":3,"title":"orca_command  <code>class-attribute</code> <code>instance-attribute</code>","text":"<pre><code>orca_command: str = Field(default='orca')\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Config"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/config.html#cspilot.config.Settings.runs_dir","level":3,"title":"runs_dir  <code>class-attribute</code> <code>instance-attribute</code>","text":"<pre><code>runs_dir: Path = Field(default=Path('runs'))\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Config"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/config.html#cspilot.config.Settings.xtb_command","level":3,"title":"xtb_command  <code>class-attribute</code> <code>instance-attribute</code>","text":"<pre><code>xtb_command: str = Field(default='xtb')\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Config"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/config.html#cspilot.config.load_settings","level":2,"title":"load_settings","text":"<pre><code>load_settings(env_file: Path | str = '.env.cspilot') -&gt; Settings\n</code></pre> Source code in <code>cspilot/config.py</code> <pre><code>def load_settings(env_file: Path | str = \".env.cspilot\") -&gt; Settings:\n    load_dotenv(env_file)\n    return Settings(\n        runs_dir=Path(os.getenv(\"CSPILOT_RUNS_DIR\", \"runs\")),\n        xtb_command=os.getenv(\"XTB_COMMAND\", \"xtb\"),\n        orca_command=os.getenv(\"ORCA_COMMAND\", \"orca\"),\n    )\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Config"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/llm.html","level":1,"title":"Llm","text":"","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Llm"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/llm.html#cspilot.llm.create_agapi_client","level":2,"title":"create_agapi_client","text":"<pre><code>create_agapi_client(base_url: str | None = None) -&gt; AsyncOpenAI\n</code></pre> <p>Create the OpenAI-compatible asynchronous AGAPI client.</p> Source code in <code>cspilot/llm.py</code> <pre><code>def create_agapi_client(base_url: str | None = None) -&gt; AsyncOpenAI:\n    \"\"\"Create the OpenAI-compatible asynchronous AGAPI client.\"\"\"\n    load_dotenv(\".env.cspilot\")\n    api_key = _require_env(\"AGAPI_API_KEY\")\n    resolved_base_url = base_url or _require_env(\"AGAPI_BASE_URL\")\n    return AsyncOpenAI(api_key=api_key, base_url=resolved_base_url)\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Llm"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/llm.html#cspilot.llm.create_agapi_model","level":2,"title":"create_agapi_model","text":"<pre><code>create_agapi_model(model: str | None = None, base_url: str | None = None) -&gt; OpenAIChatCompletionsModel\n</code></pre> <p>Create an Agents SDK chat completions model backed by AGAPI.</p> Source code in <code>cspilot/llm.py</code> <pre><code>def create_agapi_model(\n    model: str | None = None,\n    base_url: str | None = None,\n) -&gt; OpenAIChatCompletionsModel:\n    \"\"\"Create an Agents SDK chat completions model backed by AGAPI.\"\"\"\n    load_dotenv(\".env.cspilot\")\n    set_tracing_disabled(disabled=True)\n    return OpenAIChatCompletionsModel(\n        model=model or _require_env(\"cspilot_MODEL\"),\n        openai_client=create_agapi_client(base_url=base_url),\n    )\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Llm"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/schemas.html","level":1,"title":"Schemas","text":"","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Schemas"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/schemas.html#cspilot.schemas.RunStatus","level":2,"title":"RunStatus  <code>module-attribute</code>","text":"<pre><code>RunStatus = Literal['ok', 'failed', 'skipped']\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Schemas"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/schemas.html#cspilot.schemas.CommandResult","level":2,"title":"CommandResult","text":"<p>               Bases: <code>BaseModel</code></p>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Schemas"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/schemas.html#cspilot.schemas.CommandResult.command","level":3,"title":"command  <code>instance-attribute</code>","text":"<pre><code>command: str\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Schemas"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/schemas.html#cspilot.schemas.CommandResult.created_at","level":3,"title":"created_at  <code>class-attribute</code> <code>instance-attribute</code>","text":"<pre><code>created_at: datetime = Field(default_factory=now)\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Schemas"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/schemas.html#cspilot.schemas.CommandResult.input_path","level":3,"title":"input_path  <code>instance-attribute</code>","text":"<pre><code>input_path: Path\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Schemas"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/schemas.html#cspilot.schemas.CommandResult.message","level":3,"title":"message  <code>class-attribute</code> <code>instance-attribute</code>","text":"<pre><code>message: str | None = None\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Schemas"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/schemas.html#cspilot.schemas.CommandResult.outputs","level":3,"title":"outputs  <code>class-attribute</code> <code>instance-attribute</code>","text":"<pre><code>outputs: dict[str, Any] = Field(default_factory=dict)\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Schemas"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/schemas.html#cspilot.schemas.CommandResult.parameters","level":3,"title":"parameters  <code>class-attribute</code> <code>instance-attribute</code>","text":"<pre><code>parameters: dict[str, Any] = Field(default_factory=dict)\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Schemas"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/schemas.html#cspilot.schemas.CommandResult.run_dir","level":3,"title":"run_dir  <code>instance-attribute</code>","text":"<pre><code>run_dir: Path\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Schemas"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/schemas.html#cspilot.schemas.CommandResult.status","level":3,"title":"status  <code>instance-attribute</code>","text":"<pre><code>status: RunStatus\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Schemas"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/schemas.html#cspilot.schemas.CommandResult.structure","level":3,"title":"structure  <code>class-attribute</code> <code>instance-attribute</code>","text":"<pre><code>structure: StructureSummary | None = None\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Schemas"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/schemas.html#cspilot.schemas.ProcessResult","level":2,"title":"ProcessResult","text":"<p>               Bases: <code>BaseModel</code></p>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Schemas"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/schemas.html#cspilot.schemas.ProcessResult.command","level":3,"title":"command  <code>instance-attribute</code>","text":"<pre><code>command: list[str]\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Schemas"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/schemas.html#cspilot.schemas.ProcessResult.returncode","level":3,"title":"returncode  <code>instance-attribute</code>","text":"<pre><code>returncode: int\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Schemas"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/schemas.html#cspilot.schemas.ProcessResult.stderr","level":3,"title":"stderr  <code>instance-attribute</code>","text":"<pre><code>stderr: str\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Schemas"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/schemas.html#cspilot.schemas.ProcessResult.stdout","level":3,"title":"stdout  <code>instance-attribute</code>","text":"<pre><code>stdout: str\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Schemas"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/schemas.html#cspilot.schemas.StructureSummary","level":2,"title":"StructureSummary","text":"<p>               Bases: <code>BaseModel</code></p>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Schemas"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/schemas.html#cspilot.schemas.StructureSummary.cell","level":3,"title":"cell  <code>instance-attribute</code>","text":"<pre><code>cell: list[list[float]]\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Schemas"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/schemas.html#cspilot.schemas.StructureSummary.center_of_mass","level":3,"title":"center_of_mass  <code>instance-attribute</code>","text":"<pre><code>center_of_mass: list[float]\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Schemas"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/schemas.html#cspilot.schemas.StructureSummary.charge","level":3,"title":"charge  <code>class-attribute</code> <code>instance-attribute</code>","text":"<pre><code>charge: float | None = None\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Schemas"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/schemas.html#cspilot.schemas.StructureSummary.formula","level":3,"title":"formula  <code>instance-attribute</code>","text":"<pre><code>formula: str\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Schemas"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/schemas.html#cspilot.schemas.StructureSummary.natoms","level":3,"title":"natoms  <code>instance-attribute</code>","text":"<pre><code>natoms: int\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Schemas"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/schemas.html#cspilot.schemas.StructureSummary.path","level":3,"title":"path  <code>instance-attribute</code>","text":"<pre><code>path: Path\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Schemas"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/schemas.html#cspilot.schemas.StructureSummary.pbc","level":3,"title":"pbc  <code>instance-attribute</code>","text":"<pre><code>pbc: tuple[bool, bool, bool]\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","Schemas"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/agents/executor.html","level":1,"title":"Executor","text":"","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","agents","Executor"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/agents/executor.html#cspilot.agents.executor.execute_plan","level":2,"title":"execute_plan","text":"<pre><code>execute_plan(plan: dict[str, Any], workdir: str) -&gt; dict[str, Any]\n</code></pre> <p>Execute a validated JSON plan only through the allowlisted tool registry.</p> Source code in <code>cspilot/agents/executor.py</code> <pre><code>def execute_plan(plan: dict[str, Any], workdir: str) -&gt; dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Execute a validated JSON plan only through the allowlisted tool registry.\"\"\"\n    root = Path(workdir)\n    root.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n    steps = plan.get(\"steps\")\n    if not isinstance(steps, list):\n        raise ValueError(\"Plan must contain a steps list.\")\n\n    _write_json(root / \"plan.json\", plan)\n    results: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n    issues: list[str] = []\n    for index, step in enumerate(steps, start=1):\n        if not isinstance(step, dict) or step.get(\"tool\") not in get_allowed_tools():\n            raise ValueError(f\"Unknown or disallowed tool in step {index}.\")\n        result = call_tool(str(step[\"tool\"]), step.get(\"args\", {}), str(root))\n        results.append(result)\n        _write_json(root / f\"step_{index:03d}_result.json\", result)\n        verification = verify_tool_result(result, str(root))\n        issues.extend(f\"Step {index}: {issue}\" for issue in verification[\"issues\"])\n\n    execution_result = {\n        \"success\": not issues,\n        \"workdir\": str(root),\n        \"plan_path\": str(root / \"plan.json\"),\n        \"steps\": results,\n        \"verification\": {\"verified\": not issues, \"issues\": issues},\n    }\n    _write_json(root / \"execution_result.json\", execution_result)\n    return execution_result\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","agents","Executor"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/agents/openai_agent.html","level":1,"title":"Openai agent","text":"","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","agents","Openai agent"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/agents/openai_agent.html#cspilot.agents.openai_agent.CHEM_INSTRUCTIONS","level":2,"title":"CHEM_INSTRUCTIONS  <code>module-attribute</code>","text":"<pre><code>CHEM_INSTRUCTIONS = 'You are a computational chemistry workflow agent.\\nUse only provided tools.\\nDo not invent energies, structures, files, or calculation results.\\nPrefer run_xtb_orca_workflow for xTB optimization followed by ORCA SP.\\nFor a new Gibbs free energy or thermochemistry calculation, use run_xtb_orca_frequency_workflow.\\nIf the user provides a molecule name and no XYZ file, use molecule_name_to_xyz_tool.\\nIf the user provides SMILES and no XYZ file, use smiles_to_xyz_tool.\\nIf the user asks for a property from previous results, use find_result_json and get_property_from_result.\\nDo not guess property values. If a property name is ambiguous, use aliases first.\\nIf no matching property is found, say it was not found and mention the searched file.\\nIf unsupported, clearly say unsupported.'\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","agents","Openai agent"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/agents/openai_agent.html#cspilot.agents.openai_agent.GENERAL_INSTRUCTIONS","level":2,"title":"GENERAL_INSTRUCTIONS  <code>module-attribute</code>","text":"<pre><code>GENERAL_INSTRUCTIONS = 'You are a planning and reporting agent.\\nProvide only generic planning and reporting using available information.\\nDo not claim to run or interpret calculations, and do not invent energies, structures, files, or results.\\nIf a computational or materials action is requested, clearly say unsupported.'\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","agents","Openai agent"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/agents/openai_agent.html#cspilot.agents.openai_agent.MATERIALS_INSTRUCTIONS","level":2,"title":"MATERIALS_INSTRUCTIONS  <code>module-attribute</code>","text":"<pre><code>MATERIALS_INSTRUCTIONS = 'You are a materials science workflow agent.\\nUse only provided tools for structure inspection and calculations.\\nYou may use AGAPI/JARVIS/materials style reasoning only if supported by available tools or returned information.\\nDo not invent energies, structures, files, database results, or calculation results.\\nPrefer run_xtb_orca_workflow for xTB optimization followed by ORCA SP.\\nFor a new Gibbs free energy or thermochemistry calculation, use run_xtb_orca_frequency_workflow.\\nIf the user provides a molecule name and no XYZ file, use molecule_name_to_xyz_tool.\\nIf the user provides SMILES and no XYZ file, use smiles_to_xyz_tool.\\nIf the user asks for a property from previous results, use find_result_json and get_property_from_result.\\nDo not guess property values. If a property name is ambiguous, use aliases first.\\nIf no matching property is found, say it was not found and mention the searched file.\\nIf a requested materials capability is not available as a tool, clearly say unsupported.'\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","agents","Openai agent"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/agents/openai_agent.html#cspilot.agents.openai_agent.PROFILE_INSTRUCTIONS","level":2,"title":"PROFILE_INSTRUCTIONS  <code>module-attribute</code>","text":"<pre><code>PROFILE_INSTRUCTIONS = {'chem': CHEM_INSTRUCTIONS, 'materials': MATERIALS_INSTRUCTIONS, 'general': GENERAL_INSTRUCTIONS}\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","agents","Openai agent"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/agents/openai_agent.html#cspilot.agents.openai_agent.create_computational_chemistry_agent","level":2,"title":"create_computational_chemistry_agent","text":"<pre><code>create_computational_chemistry_agent(profile: str = 'chem', model: str | None = None, base_url: str | None = None) -&gt; Agent\n</code></pre> Source code in <code>cspilot/agents/openai_agent.py</code> <pre><code>def create_computational_chemistry_agent(\n    profile: str = \"chem\",\n    model: str | None = None,\n    base_url: str | None = None,\n) -&gt; Agent:\n    instructions = _profile_instructions(profile)\n    return Agent(\n        name=\"cspilot\",\n        instructions=instructions,\n        model=create_agapi_model(model=model, base_url=base_url),\n        tools=_profile_tools(profile),\n    )\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","agents","Openai agent"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/agents/openai_agent.html#cspilot.agents.openai_agent.run_agent_request","level":2,"title":"run_agent_request  <code>async</code>","text":"<pre><code>run_agent_request(request: str, workdir: Path | str, model: str | None = None, base_url: str | None = None, profile: str = 'chem') -&gt; dict[str, Any]\n</code></pre> Source code in <code>cspilot/agents/openai_agent.py</code> <pre><code>async def run_agent_request(\n    request: str,\n    workdir: Path | str,\n    model: str | None = None,\n    base_url: str | None = None,\n    profile: str = \"chem\",\n) -&gt; dict[str, Any]:\n    workdir = Path(workdir)\n    workdir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n    token = set_agent_workdir(workdir)\n    try:\n        result = await Runner.run(\n            create_computational_chemistry_agent(\n                profile=profile,\n                model=model,\n                base_url=base_url,\n            ),\n            request,\n        )\n        tool_results = _collect_tool_results(result.new_items)\n        verification = _verify_results(tool_results, str(workdir))\n        report = make_report(request, tool_results, verification)\n        payload = {\n            \"request\": request,\n            \"workdir\": str(workdir),\n            \"agent_profile\": profile,\n            \"model\": model,\n            \"base_url\": base_url,\n            \"model_output\": str(result.final_output),\n            \"tool_results\": tool_results,\n            \"verification\": verification,\n            \"final_output\": report,\n        }\n        result_path = workdir / \"agent_result.json\"\n        payload[\"result_path\"] = str(result_path)\n        result_path.write_text(json.dumps(payload, indent=2) + \"\\n\", encoding=\"utf-8\")\n        return payload\n    finally:\n        reset_agent_workdir(token)\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","agents","Openai agent"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/agents/planner.html","level":1,"title":"Planner","text":"","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","agents","Planner"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/agents/planner.html#cspilot.agents.planner.ExecutionPlan","level":2,"title":"ExecutionPlan","text":"<p>               Bases: <code>BaseModel</code></p>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","agents","Planner"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/agents/planner.html#cspilot.agents.planner.ExecutionPlan.steps","level":3,"title":"steps  <code>class-attribute</code> <code>instance-attribute</code>","text":"<pre><code>steps: list[PlanStep] = Field(default_factory=list)\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","agents","Planner"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/agents/planner.html#cspilot.agents.planner.PlanStep","level":2,"title":"PlanStep","text":"<p>               Bases: <code>BaseModel</code></p>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","agents","Planner"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/agents/planner.html#cspilot.agents.planner.PlanStep.args","level":3,"title":"args  <code>class-attribute</code> <code>instance-attribute</code>","text":"<pre><code>args: dict[str, Any] = Field(default_factory=dict)\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","agents","Planner"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/agents/planner.html#cspilot.agents.planner.PlanStep.tool","level":3,"title":"tool  <code>instance-attribute</code>","text":"<pre><code>tool: str\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","agents","Planner"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/agents/planner.html#cspilot.agents.planner.create_plan","level":2,"title":"create_plan  <code>async</code>","text":"<pre><code>create_plan(user_request: str, model: str | None = None, base_url: str | None = None, profile: str = 'chem') -&gt; dict[str, Any]\n</code></pre> <p>Generate and validate an explicit allowlisted JSON execution plan.</p> Source code in <code>cspilot/agents/planner.py</code> <pre><code>async def create_plan(\n    user_request: str,\n    model: str | None = None,\n    base_url: str | None = None,\n    profile: str = \"chem\",\n) -&gt; dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Generate and validate an explicit allowlisted JSON execution plan.\"\"\"\n    selected_profile = get_profile(profile)\n    allowed_tools = get_allowed_tools(profile, user_request)\n    instructions = f\"\"\"{selected_profile.system_prompt}\n\nProduce an execution plan as strict JSON only.\nThe output schema is {{\"steps\": [{{\"tool\": \"...\", \"args\": {{}}}}]}}.\nChoose only these allowed tools: {allowed_tools}.\nAllowed tool groups for this profile: {selected_profile.allowed_tool_groups}.\nDefault output style: {selected_profile.default_output_style}.\nPreserve user-provided filenames exactly.\nUse defaults when needed: charge=0, mult=1, method=\"r2scan-3c\", basis=\"def2-SVP\".\nPrefer run_xtb_orca_workflow for xTB optimization followed by ORCA SP.\nDo not add shell commands or unsupported tools.\nIf the allowed tools list is empty, return {{\"steps\": []}}.\"\"\"\n    agent = Agent(\n        name=\"cspilot_planner\",\n        instructions=instructions,\n        model=create_agapi_model(model=model, base_url=base_url),\n        tools=[],\n        output_type=AgentOutputSchema(ExecutionPlan, strict_json_schema=False),\n    )\n    result = await Runner.run(agent, user_request)\n    plan = (\n        result.final_output\n        if isinstance(result.final_output, ExecutionPlan)\n        else ExecutionPlan.model_validate(result.final_output)\n    )\n    for step in plan.steps:\n        if step.tool not in allowed_tools:\n            raise ValueError(f\"Planner returned disallowed tool: {step.tool}\")\n    return plan.model_dump(mode=\"json\")\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","agents","Planner"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/agents/reporter.html","level":1,"title":"Reporter","text":"","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","agents","Reporter"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/agents/reporter.html#cspilot.agents.reporter.generate_report","level":2,"title":"generate_report","text":"<pre><code>generate_report(user_request: str, plan: dict[str, Any], execution_result: dict[str, Any], verification_result: dict[str, Any], html: bool = False, profile: str = 'chem') -&gt; str\n</code></pre> <p>Create a deterministic Markdown or HTML execution report.</p> Source code in <code>cspilot/agents/reporter.py</code> <pre><code>def generate_report(\n    user_request: str,\n    plan: dict[str, Any],\n    execution_result: dict[str, Any],\n    verification_result: dict[str, Any],\n    html: bool = False,\n    profile: str = \"chem\",\n) -&gt; str:\n    \"\"\"Create a deterministic Markdown or HTML execution report.\"\"\"\n    selected_profile = get_profile(profile)\n    sections = _report_sections(\n        user_request,\n        plan,\n        execution_result,\n        verification_result,\n        profile,\n        selected_profile.default_output_style,\n    )\n    if html:\n        return _as_html(sections)\n    return _as_markdown(sections)\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","agents","Reporter"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/agents/reporter.html#cspilot.agents.reporter.make_report","level":2,"title":"make_report","text":"<pre><code>make_report(user_request: str, tool_results: list[dict[str, Any]], verification: dict[str, Any]) -&gt; str\n</code></pre> <p>Build a plain-text report strictly from returned tool data.</p> Source code in <code>cspilot/agents/reporter.py</code> <pre><code>def make_report(\n    user_request: str,\n    tool_results: list[dict[str, Any]],\n    verification: dict[str, Any],\n) -&gt; str:\n    \"\"\"Build a plain-text report strictly from returned tool data.\"\"\"\n    lines = [f\"Request: {user_request}\"]\n    if verification.get(\"workdir\"):\n        lines.append(f\"Workdir: {verification['workdir']}\")\n    if not tool_results:\n        lines.append(\"No tool results were returned.\")\n    for index, result in enumerate(tool_results, start=1):\n        name = str(result.get(\"tool_name\", f\"step_{index}\"))\n        status = result.get(\"status\", \"returned\")\n        lines.append(f\"Step {index} ({name}): {status}.\")\n        workdir = result.get(\"workdir\") or result.get(\"run_dir\")\n        if workdir and workdir != verification.get(\"workdir\"):\n            lines.append(f\"Workdir: {workdir}\")\n        for key, value in _reported_values(result):\n            lines.append(f\"{key}: {value}\")\n        files = _generated_files(result)\n        if files:\n            lines.append(\"Generated files: \" + \", \".join(files))\n\n    if verification.get(\"verified\"):\n        lines.append(\"Verification: passed.\")\n    else:\n        lines.append(\"Verification: failed or incomplete.\")\n        for issue in verification.get(\"issues\", []):\n            lines.append(f\"Issue: {issue}\")\n    return \"\\n\".join(lines)\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","agents","Reporter"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/agents/verifier.html","level":1,"title":"Verifier","text":"","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","agents","Verifier"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/agents/verifier.html#cspilot.agents.verifier.verify_execution","level":2,"title":"verify_execution","text":"<pre><code>verify_execution(execution_result: dict[str, Any], workdir: str) -&gt; dict[str, Any]\n</code></pre> <p>Verify an executor result and all of its returned step data.</p> Source code in <code>cspilot/agents/verifier.py</code> <pre><code>def verify_execution(execution_result: dict[str, Any], workdir: str) -&gt; dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Verify an executor result and all of its returned step data.\"\"\"\n    issues: list[str] = []\n    if execution_result.get(\"success\") is not True:\n        issues.append(\"Execution result did not report success=true.\")\n\n    steps = execution_result.get(\"steps\", [])\n    if not isinstance(steps, list):\n        issues.append(\"Execution result steps are missing or invalid.\")\n        steps = []\n\n    for index, step in enumerate(steps, start=1):\n        if not isinstance(step, dict):\n            issues.append(f\"Step {index} result is not a JSON object.\")\n            continue\n        if \"success\" in step and step[\"success\"] is not True:\n            issues.append(f\"Step {index} did not report success=true.\")\n        verification = verify_tool_result(step, workdir)\n        issues.extend(f\"Step {index}: {issue}\" for issue in verification[\"issues\"])\n        _verify_step_xyz(step, Path(workdir), index, issues)\n\n    return {\"verified\": not issues, \"issues\": _deduplicate(issues)}\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","agents","Verifier"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/agents/verifier.html#cspilot.agents.verifier.verify_tool_result","level":2,"title":"verify_tool_result","text":"<pre><code>verify_tool_result(result: dict[str, Any], workdir: str) -&gt; dict[str, Any]\n</code></pre> <p>Verify recorded tool output without inferring any scientific values.</p> Source code in <code>cspilot/agents/verifier.py</code> <pre><code>def verify_tool_result(result: dict[str, Any], workdir: str) -&gt; dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Verify recorded tool output without inferring any scientific values.\"\"\"\n    issues: list[str] = []\n    root = Path(workdir)\n\n    for key, value in _walk(result):\n        normalized_key = key.lower()\n        if normalized_key == \"success\" and value is False:\n            issues.append(\"Tool returned success=false.\")\n        if normalized_key == \"status\" and value in {\"failed\", \"skipped\"}:\n            issues.append(f\"Tool status is {value}.\")\n        if normalized_key in {\"error\", \"error_message\"} and value not in (None, \"\"):\n            issues.append(f\"Tool returned {key}: {value}\")\n        if _is_energy_key(normalized_key) and value is not None and not _numeric_value(value):\n            issues.append(f\"Energy value for '{key}' is not numeric.\")\n        if _is_file_key(normalized_key) and isinstance(value, str):\n            path = _existing_path(value, root)\n            if path is None:\n                issues.append(f\"Returned file does not exist: {value}\")\n\n    _verify_expected_outputs(result, root, issues)\n    return {\"verified\": not issues, \"issues\": _deduplicate(issues)}\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","agents","Verifier"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/prompts/system_prompts.html","level":1,"title":"System prompts","text":"","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","prompts","System prompts"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/prompts/system_prompts.html#cspilot.prompts.system_prompts.PROFILES","level":2,"title":"PROFILES  <code>module-attribute</code>","text":"<pre><code>PROFILES = {'chem': PromptProfile(system_prompt='You are a computational chemistry planning assistant. Use only ASE, xTB, ORCA/OPI, and MACE calculation tools that are provided. Prefer run_xtb_orca_workflow for xTB optimization followed by ORCA single point. Never invent structures, energies, files, or completed calculations.', allowed_tool_groups=('chemistry',), default_output_style='markdown'), 'materials': PromptProfile(system_prompt='You are a materials-query planning assistant. Use only available AGAPI/JARVIS/materials query tools. Do not claim database matches, materials properties, or files unless a tool returns them.', allowed_tool_groups=('materials',), default_output_style='markdown'), 'analysis': PromptProfile(system_prompt='You are a calculation-result analysis assistant. Use available ORCA result JSON query tools only. Multiwfn tools are not available unless explicitly provided in the allowed tool list. Never infer absent properties.', allowed_tool_groups=('analysis',), default_output_style='markdown'), 'thermo': PromptProfile(system_prompt='You are a thermochemistry reporting assistant. Use provided stored-result query tools for thermochemistry values. Heat-of-combustion calculations are unsupported unless an allowed tool is provided. Never invent thermochemical values.', allowed_tool_groups=('thermo',), default_output_style='markdown'), 'general': PromptProfile(system_prompt='You are a general planning assistant. Do not use calculation tools. A materials query tool may be used only when the user explicitly requests an AGAPI, JARVIS, or materials search. State clearly when requested functionality is unavailable.', allowed_tool_groups=(), default_output_style='concise_markdown')}\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","prompts","System prompts"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/prompts/system_prompts.html#cspilot.prompts.system_prompts.PromptProfile","level":2,"title":"PromptProfile  <code>dataclass</code>","text":"<pre><code>PromptProfile(system_prompt: str, allowed_tool_groups: tuple[str, ...], default_output_style: str)\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","prompts","System prompts"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/prompts/system_prompts.html#cspilot.prompts.system_prompts.PromptProfile.allowed_tool_groups","level":3,"title":"allowed_tool_groups  <code>instance-attribute</code>","text":"<pre><code>allowed_tool_groups: tuple[str, ...]\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","prompts","System prompts"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/prompts/system_prompts.html#cspilot.prompts.system_prompts.PromptProfile.default_output_style","level":3,"title":"default_output_style  <code>instance-attribute</code>","text":"<pre><code>default_output_style: str\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","prompts","System prompts"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/prompts/system_prompts.html#cspilot.prompts.system_prompts.PromptProfile.system_prompt","level":3,"title":"system_prompt  <code>instance-attribute</code>","text":"<pre><code>system_prompt: str\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","prompts","System prompts"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/prompts/system_prompts.html#cspilot.prompts.system_prompts.allowed_group_names","level":2,"title":"allowed_group_names","text":"<pre><code>allowed_group_names(profile: str, user_request: str = '') -&gt; tuple[str, ...]\n</code></pre> Source code in <code>cspilot/prompts/system_prompts.py</code> <pre><code>def allowed_group_names(profile: str, user_request: str = \"\") -&gt; tuple[str, ...]:\n    selected = get_profile(profile)\n    if profile == \"general\" and _explicit_materials_query(user_request):\n        return (\"materials\",)\n    return selected.allowed_tool_groups\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","prompts","System prompts"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/prompts/system_prompts.html#cspilot.prompts.system_prompts.get_profile","level":2,"title":"get_profile","text":"<pre><code>get_profile(profile: str) -&gt; PromptProfile\n</code></pre> Source code in <code>cspilot/prompts/system_prompts.py</code> <pre><code>def get_profile(profile: str) -&gt; PromptProfile:\n    try:\n        return PROFILES[profile]\n    except KeyError as exc:\n        allowed = \", \".join(PROFILES)\n        raise ValueError(f\"Unknown profile '{profile}'. Expected one of: {allowed}\") from exc\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","prompts","System prompts"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/agapi_materials_tools.html","level":1,"title":"Agapi materials tools","text":"","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Agapi materials tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/agapi_materials_tools.html#cspilot.tools.agapi_materials_tools.agapi_materials_query","level":2,"title":"agapi_materials_query","text":"<pre><code>agapi_materials_query(query: str, render_html: bool = False) -&gt; dict[str, Any]\n</code></pre> <p>Query optional AGAPI materials capabilities when the package is installed.</p> Source code in <code>cspilot/tools/agapi_materials_tools.py</code> <pre><code>def agapi_materials_query(query: str, render_html: bool = False) -&gt; dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Query optional AGAPI materials capabilities when the package is installed.\"\"\"\n    load_dotenv(\".env.cspilot\")\n    try:\n        from agapi.agents import AGAPIAgent\n    except ImportError:\n        return {\n            \"success\": False,\n            \"query\": query,\n            \"error\": \"AGAPIAgent is unavailable; install the optional agapi package.\",\n            \"source\": \"AGAPI\",\n        }\n\n    api_key = os.getenv(\"AGAPI_API_KEY\")\n    if not api_key:\n        return {\n            \"success\": False,\n            \"query\": query,\n            \"error\": \"AGAPI_API_KEY is not configured.\",\n            \"source\": \"AGAPI\",\n        }\n\n    try:\n        result = AGAPIAgent(api_key=api_key).query_sync(query, render_html=render_html)\n    except Exception as exc:\n        return {\n            \"success\": False,\n            \"query\": query,\n            \"error\": f\"AGAPI query failed: {exc}\",\n            \"source\": \"AGAPI\",\n        }\n\n    # AGAPIAgent displays rendered HTML in notebook contexts but returns its\n    # response envelope, rather than the generated HTML markup.\n    html = None\n    text = str(result) if result is not None else None\n    return {\n        \"success\": True,\n        \"query\": query,\n        \"html\": html,\n        \"text\": text,\n        \"source\": \"AGAPI\",\n    }\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Agapi materials tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/agent_tools.html","level":1,"title":"Agent tools","text":"","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Agent tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/agent_tools.html#cspilot.tools.agent_tools.agapi_materials_query_tool","level":2,"title":"agapi_materials_query_tool","text":"<pre><code>agapi_materials_query_tool(query: str, render_html: bool = False) -&gt; dict[str, Any]\n</code></pre> <p>Query optional AGAPI materials search capabilities.</p> <p>Args:     query: Natural-language materials query.     render_html: Whether AGAPI should return an HTML representation.</p> Source code in <code>cspilot/tools/agent_tools.py</code> <pre><code>@function_tool\ndef agapi_materials_query_tool(query: str, render_html: bool = False) -&gt; dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Query optional AGAPI materials search capabilities.\n\n    Args:\n        query: Natural-language materials query.\n        render_html: Whether AGAPI should return an HTML representation.\n    \"\"\"\n    return agapi_materials_query(query, render_html=render_html)\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Agent tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/agent_tools.html#cspilot.tools.agent_tools.canonicalize_smiles_tool","level":2,"title":"canonicalize_smiles_tool","text":"<pre><code>canonicalize_smiles_tool(smiles: str) -&gt; dict[str, Any]\n</code></pre> <p>Canonicalize a SMILES string using RDKit.</p> <p>Args:     smiles: SMILES string to canonicalize.</p> Source code in <code>cspilot/tools/agent_tools.py</code> <pre><code>@function_tool\ndef canonicalize_smiles_tool(smiles: str) -&gt; dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Canonicalize a SMILES string using RDKit.\n\n    Args:\n        smiles: SMILES string to canonicalize.\n    \"\"\"\n    return canonicalize_smiles(smiles)\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Agent tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/agent_tools.html#cspilot.tools.agent_tools.find_result_json_agent_tool","level":2,"title":"find_result_json_agent_tool","text":"<pre><code>find_result_json_agent_tool(workdir: str, latest: bool = True) -&gt; dict[str, Any]\n</code></pre> <p>Find calculation result JSON files from a previous run directory.</p> <p>Args:     workdir: Directory to search recursively.     latest: If true, identify the newest matched result file.</p> Source code in <code>cspilot/tools/agent_tools.py</code> <pre><code>@function_tool(name_override=\"find_result_json\")\ndef find_result_json_agent_tool(workdir: str, latest: bool = True) -&gt; dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Find calculation result JSON files from a previous run directory.\n\n    Args:\n        workdir: Directory to search recursively.\n        latest: If true, identify the newest matched result file.\n    \"\"\"\n    return find_result_json(workdir, latest=latest)\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Agent tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/agent_tools.html#cspilot.tools.agent_tools.find_result_json_tool","level":2,"title":"find_result_json_tool","text":"<pre><code>find_result_json_tool(workdir: str, latest: bool = True) -&gt; dict[str, Any]\n</code></pre> <p>Find calculation result JSON files in a run directory.</p> <p>Args:     workdir: Directory to search recursively.     latest: If true, identify the newest matched result file.</p> Source code in <code>cspilot/tools/agent_tools.py</code> <pre><code>@function_tool\ndef find_result_json_tool(workdir: str, latest: bool = True) -&gt; dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Find calculation result JSON files in a run directory.\n\n    Args:\n        workdir: Directory to search recursively.\n        latest: If true, identify the newest matched result file.\n    \"\"\"\n    return find_result_json(workdir, latest=latest)\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Agent tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/agent_tools.html#cspilot.tools.agent_tools.get_property_from_result_agent_tool","level":2,"title":"get_property_from_result_agent_tool","text":"<pre><code>get_property_from_result_agent_tool(path: str, property_name: str) -&gt; dict[str, Any]\n</code></pre> <p>Extract a requested property from a previous calculation result JSON file.</p> <p>Args:     path: Path to a result JSON file.     property_name: Requested property name, for example Gibbs free energy.</p> Source code in <code>cspilot/tools/agent_tools.py</code> <pre><code>@function_tool(name_override=\"get_property_from_result\")\ndef get_property_from_result_agent_tool(path: str, property_name: str) -&gt; dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Extract a requested property from a previous calculation result JSON file.\n\n    Args:\n        path: Path to a result JSON file.\n        property_name: Requested property name, for example Gibbs free energy.\n    \"\"\"\n    return get_property_from_result(path, property_name)\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Agent tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/agent_tools.html#cspilot.tools.agent_tools.get_property_from_result_tool","level":2,"title":"get_property_from_result_tool","text":"<pre><code>get_property_from_result_tool(path: str, property_name: str) -&gt; dict[str, Any]\n</code></pre> <p>Extract a stored property from a result JSON file using supported aliases.</p> <p>Args:     path: Path to a result JSON file.     property_name: Requested property name, for example Gibbs free energy.</p> Source code in <code>cspilot/tools/agent_tools.py</code> <pre><code>@function_tool\ndef get_property_from_result_tool(path: str, property_name: str) -&gt; dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Extract a stored property from a result JSON file using supported aliases.\n\n    Args:\n        path: Path to a result JSON file.\n        property_name: Requested property name, for example Gibbs free energy.\n    \"\"\"\n    return get_property_from_result(path, property_name)\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Agent tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/agent_tools.html#cspilot.tools.agent_tools.inspect_structure","level":2,"title":"inspect_structure","text":"<pre><code>inspect_structure(xyz_path: str) -&gt; dict[str, Any]\n</code></pre> <p>Inspect an XYZ structure and report values directly computed by ASE.</p> <p>Args:     xyz_path: Path to an XYZ structure file.</p> Source code in <code>cspilot/tools/agent_tools.py</code> <pre><code>@function_tool\ndef inspect_structure(xyz_path: str) -&gt; dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Inspect an XYZ structure and report values directly computed by ASE.\n\n    Args:\n        xyz_path: Path to an XYZ structure file.\n    \"\"\"\n    try:\n        summary = summarize_structure(Path(xyz_path).expanduser())\n        return {\"status\": \"ok\", \"structure\": summary.model_dump(mode=\"json\")}\n    except Exception as exc:\n        return _failure(exc)\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Agent tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/agent_tools.html#cspilot.tools.agent_tools.molecule_name_to_smiles_tool","level":2,"title":"molecule_name_to_smiles_tool","text":"<pre><code>molecule_name_to_smiles_tool(name: str) -&gt; dict[str, Any]\n</code></pre> <p>Look up the SMILES representation of a molecule name from PubChem.</p> <p>Args:     name: Common or systematic molecule name.</p> Source code in <code>cspilot/tools/agent_tools.py</code> <pre><code>@function_tool\ndef molecule_name_to_smiles_tool(name: str) -&gt; dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Look up the SMILES representation of a molecule name from PubChem.\n\n    Args:\n        name: Common or systematic molecule name.\n    \"\"\"\n    return molecule_name_to_smiles(name)\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Agent tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/agent_tools.html#cspilot.tools.agent_tools.molecule_name_to_xyz_tool","level":2,"title":"molecule_name_to_xyz_tool","text":"<pre><code>molecule_name_to_xyz_tool(name: str, output_path: str, num_confs: int = 20) -&gt; dict[str, Any]\n</code></pre> <p>Resolve a molecule name through PubChem and write an RDKit XYZ structure.</p> <p>Args:     name: Common or systematic molecule name.     output_path: Output XYZ file path.     num_confs: Number of conformers to generate.</p> Source code in <code>cspilot/tools/agent_tools.py</code> <pre><code>@function_tool\ndef molecule_name_to_xyz_tool(\n    name: str,\n    output_path: str,\n    num_confs: int = 20,\n) -&gt; dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Resolve a molecule name through PubChem and write an RDKit XYZ structure.\n\n    Args:\n        name: Common or systematic molecule name.\n        output_path: Output XYZ file path.\n        num_confs: Number of conformers to generate.\n    \"\"\"\n    return molecule_name_to_xyz(name, output_path, num_confs=num_confs)\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Agent tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/agent_tools.html#cspilot.tools.agent_tools.reset_agent_workdir","level":2,"title":"reset_agent_workdir","text":"<pre><code>reset_agent_workdir(token: Token[Path]) -&gt; None\n</code></pre> Source code in <code>cspilot/tools/agent_tools.py</code> <pre><code>def reset_agent_workdir(token: Token[Path]) -&gt; None:\n    _agent_workdir.reset(token)\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Agent tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/agent_tools.html#cspilot.tools.agent_tools.run_mace_optimize","level":2,"title":"run_mace_optimize","text":"<pre><code>run_mace_optimize(xyz_path: str, model_path: str, fmax: float = 0.05, steps: int = 200) -&gt; dict[str, Any]\n</code></pre> <p>Run MACE geometry optimization on an XYZ structure.</p> <p>Args:     xyz_path: Path to an XYZ structure file.     model_path: Path to a MACE model file.     fmax: Force convergence threshold in eV/A.     steps: Maximum optimization steps.</p> Source code in <code>cspilot/tools/agent_tools.py</code> <pre><code>@function_tool\ndef run_mace_optimize(\n    xyz_path: str,\n    model_path: str,\n    fmax: float = 0.05,\n    steps: int = 200,\n) -&gt; dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Run MACE geometry optimization on an XYZ structure.\n\n    Args:\n        xyz_path: Path to an XYZ structure file.\n        model_path: Path to a MACE model file.\n        fmax: Force convergence threshold in eV/A.\n        steps: Maximum optimization steps.\n    \"\"\"\n    try:\n        run_dir = make_run_dir(_agent_workdir.get(), \"mace-opt\")\n        run_input = copy_input(Path(xyz_path).expanduser(), run_dir)\n        ok, message, outputs = optimize_with_mace(\n            run_input,\n            run_dir,\n            Path(model_path).expanduser(),\n            fmax=fmax,\n            steps=steps,\n        )\n        return {\n            \"status\": \"ok\" if ok else \"skipped\",\n            \"message\": message,\n            \"run_dir\": str(run_dir),\n            \"outputs\": outputs,\n        }\n    except Exception as exc:\n        return _failure(exc)\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Agent tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/agent_tools.html#cspilot.tools.agent_tools.run_orca_single_point","level":2,"title":"run_orca_single_point","text":"<pre><code>run_orca_single_point(xyz_path: str, method: str, basis: str, charge: int = 0, mult: int = 1, nprocs: int = 1) -&gt; dict[str, Any]\n</code></pre> <p>Run an ORCA single-point calculation using OPI.</p> <p>Args:     xyz_path: Path to an XYZ structure file.     method: ORCA method keyword.     basis: ORCA basis keyword.     charge: Molecular charge.     mult: Spin multiplicity.     nprocs: Number of ORCA processes.</p> Source code in <code>cspilot/tools/agent_tools.py</code> <pre><code>@function_tool\ndef run_orca_single_point(\n    xyz_path: str,\n    method: str,\n    basis: str,\n    charge: int = 0,\n    mult: int = 1,\n    nprocs: int = 1,\n) -&gt; dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Run an ORCA single-point calculation using OPI.\n\n    Args:\n        xyz_path: Path to an XYZ structure file.\n        method: ORCA method keyword.\n        basis: ORCA basis keyword.\n        charge: Molecular charge.\n        mult: Spin multiplicity.\n        nprocs: Number of ORCA processes.\n    \"\"\"\n    try:\n        settings = load_settings()\n        run_dir = make_run_dir(_agent_workdir.get(), \"orca-sp\")\n        return orca_single_point(\n            xyz_path=Path(xyz_path).expanduser(),\n            workdir=run_dir,\n            method=method,\n            basis=basis,\n            charge=charge,\n            mult=mult,\n            nprocs=nprocs,\n            orca_command=settings.orca_command,\n        )\n    except Exception as exc:\n        return _failure(exc)\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Agent tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/agent_tools.html#cspilot.tools.agent_tools.run_xtb_optimize","level":2,"title":"run_xtb_optimize","text":"<pre><code>run_xtb_optimize(xyz_path: str, charge: int = 0, uhf: int = 0) -&gt; dict[str, Any]\n</code></pre> <p>Run xTB geometry optimization on an XYZ structure.</p> <p>Args:     xyz_path: Path to an XYZ structure file.     charge: Molecular charge.     uhf: Number of unpaired electrons.</p> Source code in <code>cspilot/tools/agent_tools.py</code> <pre><code>@function_tool\ndef run_xtb_optimize(xyz_path: str, charge: int = 0, uhf: int = 0) -&gt; dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Run xTB geometry optimization on an XYZ structure.\n\n    Args:\n        xyz_path: Path to an XYZ structure file.\n        charge: Molecular charge.\n        uhf: Number of unpaired electrons.\n    \"\"\"\n    try:\n        settings = load_settings()\n        run_dir = make_run_dir(_agent_workdir.get(), \"xtb-opt\")\n        run_input = copy_input(Path(xyz_path).expanduser(), run_dir)\n        ok, message, process, outputs = optimize_with_xtb(\n            run_input,\n            run_dir,\n            settings,\n            charge,\n            uhf,\n        )\n        return {\n            \"status\": \"ok\" if ok else (\"failed\" if process is not None else \"skipped\"),\n            \"message\": message,\n            \"run_dir\": str(run_dir),\n            \"outputs\": outputs,\n            \"process\": process.model_dump(mode=\"json\") if process is not None else None,\n        }\n    except Exception as exc:\n        return _failure(exc)\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Agent tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/agent_tools.html#cspilot.tools.agent_tools.run_xtb_orca_frequency_workflow","level":2,"title":"run_xtb_orca_frequency_workflow","text":"<pre><code>run_xtb_orca_frequency_workflow(xyz_path: str, method: str = 'r2scan-3c', basis: str = 'def2-SVP', charge: int = 0, mult: int = 1, uhf: int = 0, nprocs: int = 1) -&gt; dict[str, Any]\n</code></pre> <p>Run xTB optimization followed by an ORCA frequency calculation using OPI.</p> <p>Args:     xyz_path: Path to an XYZ structure file.     method: ORCA method keyword.     basis: ORCA basis keyword.     charge: Molecular charge.     mult: Spin multiplicity.     uhf: Number of unpaired electrons for xTB.     nprocs: Number of ORCA processes.</p> Source code in <code>cspilot/tools/agent_tools.py</code> <pre><code>@function_tool\ndef run_xtb_orca_frequency_workflow(\n    xyz_path: str,\n    method: str = \"r2scan-3c\",\n    basis: str = \"def2-SVP\",\n    charge: int = 0,\n    mult: int = 1,\n    uhf: int = 0,\n    nprocs: int = 1,\n) -&gt; dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Run xTB optimization followed by an ORCA frequency calculation using OPI.\n\n    Args:\n        xyz_path: Path to an XYZ structure file.\n        method: ORCA method keyword.\n        basis: ORCA basis keyword.\n        charge: Molecular charge.\n        mult: Spin multiplicity.\n        uhf: Number of unpaired electrons for xTB.\n        nprocs: Number of ORCA processes.\n    \"\"\"\n    try:\n        settings = load_settings().model_copy(update={\"runs_dir\": _agent_workdir.get()})\n        return run_xtb_to_orca_freq(\n            input_xyz=Path(xyz_path).expanduser(),\n            charge=charge,\n            mult=mult,\n            method=method,\n            basis=basis,\n            uhf=uhf,\n            nprocs=nprocs,\n            settings=settings,\n        )\n    except Exception as exc:\n        return _failure(exc)\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Agent tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/agent_tools.html#cspilot.tools.agent_tools.run_xtb_orca_workflow","level":2,"title":"run_xtb_orca_workflow","text":"<pre><code>run_xtb_orca_workflow(xyz_path: str, method: str = 'r2scan-3c', basis: str = 'def2-SVP', charge: int = 0, mult: int = 1, uhf: int = 0, nprocs: int = 1) -&gt; dict[str, Any]\n</code></pre> <p>Run xTB optimization followed by an ORCA single point using OPI.</p> <p>Args:     xyz_path: Path to an XYZ structure file.     method: ORCA method keyword.     basis: ORCA basis keyword.     charge: Molecular charge.     mult: Spin multiplicity.     uhf: Number of unpaired electrons for xTB.     nprocs: Number of ORCA processes.</p> Source code in <code>cspilot/tools/agent_tools.py</code> <pre><code>@function_tool\ndef run_xtb_orca_workflow(\n    xyz_path: str,\n    method: str = \"r2scan-3c\",\n    basis: str = \"def2-SVP\",\n    charge: int = 0,\n    mult: int = 1,\n    uhf: int = 0,\n    nprocs: int = 1,\n) -&gt; dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Run xTB optimization followed by an ORCA single point using OPI.\n\n    Args:\n        xyz_path: Path to an XYZ structure file.\n        method: ORCA method keyword.\n        basis: ORCA basis keyword.\n        charge: Molecular charge.\n        mult: Spin multiplicity.\n        uhf: Number of unpaired electrons for xTB.\n        nprocs: Number of ORCA processes.\n    \"\"\"\n    try:\n        settings = load_settings().model_copy(update={\"runs_dir\": _agent_workdir.get()})\n        return run_xtb_to_orca_sp(\n            input_xyz=Path(xyz_path).expanduser(),\n            charge=charge,\n            mult=mult,\n            method=method,\n            basis=basis,\n            uhf=uhf,\n            nprocs=nprocs,\n            settings=settings,\n        )\n    except Exception as exc:\n        return _failure(exc)\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Agent tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/agent_tools.html#cspilot.tools.agent_tools.set_agent_workdir","level":2,"title":"set_agent_workdir","text":"<pre><code>set_agent_workdir(workdir: Path | str) -&gt; Token[Path]\n</code></pre> Source code in <code>cspilot/tools/agent_tools.py</code> <pre><code>def set_agent_workdir(workdir: Path | str) -&gt; Token[Path]:\n    workdir = Path(workdir)\n    workdir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n    return _agent_workdir.set(workdir)\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Agent tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/agent_tools.html#cspilot.tools.agent_tools.smiles_to_xyz_tool","level":2,"title":"smiles_to_xyz_tool","text":"<pre><code>smiles_to_xyz_tool(smiles: str, output_path: str, num_confs: int = 20, forcefield: str = 'MMFF') -&gt; dict[str, Any]\n</code></pre> <p>Create a minimized XYZ structure from SMILES with RDKit.</p> <p>Args:     smiles: Input SMILES string.     output_path: Output XYZ file path.     num_confs: Number of conformers to generate.     forcefield: Optimization forcefield, MMFF or UFF.</p> Source code in <code>cspilot/tools/agent_tools.py</code> <pre><code>@function_tool\ndef smiles_to_xyz_tool(\n    smiles: str,\n    output_path: str,\n    num_confs: int = 20,\n    forcefield: str = \"MMFF\",\n) -&gt; dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Create a minimized XYZ structure from SMILES with RDKit.\n\n    Args:\n        smiles: Input SMILES string.\n        output_path: Output XYZ file path.\n        num_confs: Number of conformers to generate.\n        forcefield: Optimization forcefield, MMFF or UFF.\n    \"\"\"\n    return smiles_to_xyz(smiles, output_path, num_confs=num_confs, forcefield=forcefield)\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Agent tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/agent_tools.html#cspilot.tools.agent_tools.validate_smiles_tool","level":2,"title":"validate_smiles_tool","text":"<pre><code>validate_smiles_tool(smiles: str) -&gt; dict[str, Any]\n</code></pre> <p>Check whether a SMILES string is valid using RDKit.</p> <p>Args:     smiles: SMILES string to validate.</p> Source code in <code>cspilot/tools/agent_tools.py</code> <pre><code>@function_tool\ndef validate_smiles_tool(smiles: str) -&gt; dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Check whether a SMILES string is valid using RDKit.\n\n    Args:\n        smiles: SMILES string to validate.\n    \"\"\"\n    return validate_smiles(smiles)\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Agent tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/ase_tools.html","level":1,"title":"Ase tools","text":"","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Ase tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/ase_tools.html#cspilot.tools.ase_tools.load_structure","level":2,"title":"load_structure","text":"<pre><code>load_structure(path: Path) -&gt; Atoms\n</code></pre> Source code in <code>cspilot/tools/ase_tools.py</code> <pre><code>def load_structure(path: Path) -&gt; Atoms:\n    return read(path)\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Ase tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/ase_tools.html#cspilot.tools.ase_tools.save_structure","level":2,"title":"save_structure","text":"<pre><code>save_structure(atoms: Atoms, path: Path) -&gt; None\n</code></pre> Source code in <code>cspilot/tools/ase_tools.py</code> <pre><code>def save_structure(atoms: Atoms, path: Path) -&gt; None:\n    write(path, atoms)\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Ase tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/ase_tools.html#cspilot.tools.ase_tools.summarize_structure","level":2,"title":"summarize_structure","text":"<pre><code>summarize_structure(path: Path) -&gt; StructureSummary\n</code></pre> Source code in <code>cspilot/tools/ase_tools.py</code> <pre><code>def summarize_structure(path: Path) -&gt; StructureSummary:\n    atoms = load_structure(path)\n    charge = atoms.get_initial_charges().sum()\n    return StructureSummary(\n        path=path,\n        formula=atoms.get_chemical_formula(),\n        natoms=len(atoms),\n        charge=float(charge) if charge else None,\n        pbc=tuple(bool(value) for value in atoms.pbc),\n        cell=atoms.cell.array.tolist(),\n        center_of_mass=atoms.get_center_of_mass().tolist(),\n    )\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Ase tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/mace_tools.html","level":1,"title":"Mace tools","text":"","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Mace tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/mace_tools.html#cspilot.tools.mace_tools.optimize_with_mace","level":2,"title":"optimize_with_mace","text":"<pre><code>optimize_with_mace(input_file: Path, run_dir: Path, model_path: Path, fmax: float = 0.05, steps: int = 200) -&gt; tuple[bool, str, dict[str, Any]]\n</code></pre> Source code in <code>cspilot/tools/mace_tools.py</code> <pre><code>def optimize_with_mace(\n    input_file: Path,\n    run_dir: Path,\n    model_path: Path,\n    fmax: float = 0.05,\n    steps: int = 200,\n) -&gt; tuple[bool, str, dict[str, Any]]:\n    try:\n        from mace.calculators import MACECalculator\n    except ImportError:\n        return False, \"Python package not found: mace-torch\", {}\n\n    if not model_path.exists():\n        return False, f\"MACE model not found: {model_path}\", {}\n\n    atoms = load_structure(input_file)\n    atoms.calc = MACECalculator(model_paths=str(model_path), device=\"cpu\", default_dtype=\"float64\")\n\n    trajectory = run_dir / \"mace_opt.traj\"\n    logfile = run_dir / \"mace_opt.log\"\n    optimizer = BFGS(atoms, trajectory=str(trajectory), logfile=str(logfile))\n    optimizer.run(fmax=fmax, steps=steps)\n\n    optimized_xyz = run_dir / \"mace_opt.xyz\"\n    save_structure(atoms, optimized_xyz)\n    return (\n        True,\n        \"MACE optimization completed\",\n        {\n            \"optimized_xyz\": str(optimized_xyz),\n            \"trajectory\": str(trajectory),\n            \"log\": str(logfile),\n            \"energy_ev\": float(atoms.get_potential_energy()),\n        },\n    )\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Mace tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/mol_tools.html","level":1,"title":"Mol tools","text":"","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Mol tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/mol_tools.html#cspilot.tools.mol_tools.canonicalize_smiles","level":2,"title":"canonicalize_smiles","text":"<pre><code>canonicalize_smiles(smiles: str) -&gt; dict[str, Any]\n</code></pre> <p>Convert a valid SMILES string to RDKit canonical SMILES.</p> Source code in <code>cspilot/tools/mol_tools.py</code> <pre><code>def canonicalize_smiles(smiles: str) -&gt; dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Convert a valid SMILES string to RDKit canonical SMILES.\"\"\"\n    molecule = Chem.MolFromSmiles(smiles)\n    if molecule is None:\n        return {\n            \"success\": False,\n            \"smiles\": smiles,\n            \"error\": \"Invalid SMILES\",\n        }\n    return {\n        \"success\": True,\n        \"smiles\": smiles,\n        \"canonical_smiles\": Chem.MolToSmiles(molecule),\n    }\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Mol tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/mol_tools.html#cspilot.tools.mol_tools.molecule_name_to_smiles","level":2,"title":"molecule_name_to_smiles","text":"<pre><code>molecule_name_to_smiles(name: str) -&gt; dict[str, Any]\n</code></pre> <p>Resolve a molecule name to a SMILES string through PubChem.</p> Source code in <code>cspilot/tools/mol_tools.py</code> <pre><code>def molecule_name_to_smiles(name: str) -&gt; dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Resolve a molecule name to a SMILES string through PubChem.\"\"\"\n    try:\n        compounds = pubchempy.get_compounds(str(name), \"name\")\n    except Exception as exc:\n        return {\n            \"success\": False,\n            \"name\": name,\n            \"error\": f\"PubChem query failed: {exc}\",\n        }\n\n    if not compounds or not compounds[0].connectivity_smiles:\n        return {\n            \"success\": False,\n            \"name\": name,\n            \"error\": \"Molecule name not found in PubChem\",\n        }\n\n    return {\n        \"success\": True,\n        \"name\": name,\n        \"smiles\": compounds[0].connectivity_smiles,\n        \"source\": \"PubChem\",\n    }\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Mol tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/mol_tools.html#cspilot.tools.mol_tools.molecule_name_to_xyz","level":2,"title":"molecule_name_to_xyz","text":"<pre><code>molecule_name_to_xyz(name: str, output_path: str, num_confs: int = 20) -&gt; dict[str, Any]\n</code></pre> <p>Resolve a name with PubChem and generate a lowest-energy XYZ structure.</p> Source code in <code>cspilot/tools/mol_tools.py</code> <pre><code>def molecule_name_to_xyz(name: str, output_path: str, num_confs: int = 20) -&gt; dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Resolve a name with PubChem and generate a lowest-energy XYZ structure.\"\"\"\n    lookup = molecule_name_to_smiles(name)\n    if not lookup[\"success\"]:\n        return lookup\n\n    result = smiles_to_xyz(\n        smiles=str(lookup[\"smiles\"]),\n        output_path=output_path,\n        num_confs=num_confs,\n    )\n    result[\"name\"] = name\n    result[\"source\"] = \"PubChem\"\n    return result\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Mol tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/mol_tools.html#cspilot.tools.mol_tools.smiles_to_xyz","level":2,"title":"smiles_to_xyz","text":"<pre><code>smiles_to_xyz(smiles: str, output_path: str, num_confs: int = 20, forcefield: str = 'MMFF') -&gt; dict[str, Any]\n</code></pre> <p>Generate and minimize 3D conformers, then write the lowest-energy XYZ.</p> Source code in <code>cspilot/tools/mol_tools.py</code> <pre><code>def smiles_to_xyz(\n    smiles: str,\n    output_path: str,\n    num_confs: int = 20,\n    forcefield: str = \"MMFF\",\n) -&gt; dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Generate and minimize 3D conformers, then write the lowest-energy XYZ.\"\"\"\n    molecule = Chem.MolFromSmiles(smiles)\n    if molecule is None:\n        return {\"success\": False, \"smiles\": smiles, \"error\": \"Invalid SMILES\"}\n    if num_confs &lt; 1:\n        return {\"success\": False, \"smiles\": smiles, \"error\": \"num_confs must be at least 1\"}\n\n    forcefield = forcefield.upper()\n    if forcefield not in {\"MMFF\", \"UFF\"}:\n        return {\n            \"success\": False,\n            \"smiles\": smiles,\n            \"error\": \"Unsupported forcefield; expected MMFF or UFF\",\n        }\n\n    canonical_smiles = Chem.MolToSmiles(molecule)\n    molecule = Chem.AddHs(molecule)\n    parameters = AllChem.ETKDGv3()\n    parameters.randomSeed = 0xF00D\n    conformer_ids = list(AllChem.EmbedMultipleConfs(molecule, numConfs=num_confs, params=parameters))\n    if not conformer_ids:\n        return {\n            \"success\": False,\n            \"smiles\": smiles,\n            \"canonical_smiles\": canonical_smiles,\n            \"error\": \"RDKit could not generate conformers\",\n        }\n\n    try:\n        if forcefield == \"MMFF\":\n            optimization_results = AllChem.MMFFOptimizeMoleculeConfs(molecule)\n        else:\n            optimization_results = AllChem.UFFOptimizeMoleculeConfs(molecule)\n    except Exception as exc:\n        return {\n            \"success\": False,\n            \"smiles\": smiles,\n            \"canonical_smiles\": canonical_smiles,\n            \"error\": f\"{forcefield} optimization failed: {exc}\",\n        }\n\n    if not optimization_results:\n        return {\n            \"success\": False,\n            \"smiles\": smiles,\n            \"canonical_smiles\": canonical_smiles,\n            \"error\": f\"{forcefield} did not produce conformer energies\",\n        }\n\n    best_conf_id, _ = min(\n        zip(conformer_ids, optimization_results, strict=True),\n        key=lambda item: item[1][1],\n    )\n    xyz_path = Path(output_path).expanduser()\n    xyz_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n    Chem.MolToXYZFile(molecule, str(xyz_path), confId=int(best_conf_id))\n    return {\n        \"success\": True,\n        \"smiles\": smiles,\n        \"canonical_smiles\": canonical_smiles,\n        \"xyz_path\": str(xyz_path),\n        \"num_atoms\": molecule.GetNumAtoms(),\n        \"forcefield\": forcefield,\n    }\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Mol tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/mol_tools.html#cspilot.tools.mol_tools.validate_smiles","level":2,"title":"validate_smiles","text":"<pre><code>validate_smiles(smiles: str) -&gt; dict[str, Any]\n</code></pre> <p>Validate a SMILES string with RDKit.</p> Source code in <code>cspilot/tools/mol_tools.py</code> <pre><code>def validate_smiles(smiles: str) -&gt; dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Validate a SMILES string with RDKit.\"\"\"\n    molecule = Chem.MolFromSmiles(smiles)\n    if molecule is None:\n        return {\n            \"success\": False,\n            \"smiles\": smiles,\n            \"valid\": False,\n            \"error\": \"Invalid SMILES\",\n        }\n    return {\n        \"success\": True,\n        \"smiles\": smiles,\n        \"valid\": True,\n        \"canonical_smiles\": Chem.MolToSmiles(molecule),\n    }\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Mol tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/opi_orca_tools.html","level":1,"title":"Opi orca tools","text":"","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Opi orca tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/opi_orca_tools.html#cspilot.tools.opi_orca_tools.TASK_FREQ","level":2,"title":"TASK_FREQ  <code>module-attribute</code>","text":"<pre><code>TASK_FREQ = 'freq'\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Opi orca tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/opi_orca_tools.html#cspilot.tools.opi_orca_tools.TASK_OPT","level":2,"title":"TASK_OPT  <code>module-attribute</code>","text":"<pre><code>TASK_OPT = 'opt'\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Opi orca tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/opi_orca_tools.html#cspilot.tools.opi_orca_tools.TASK_SP","level":2,"title":"TASK_SP  <code>module-attribute</code>","text":"<pre><code>TASK_SP = 'sp'\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Opi orca tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/opi_orca_tools.html#cspilot.tools.opi_orca_tools.opi_available","level":2,"title":"opi_available","text":"<pre><code>opi_available() -&gt; bool\n</code></pre> Source code in <code>cspilot/tools/opi_orca_tools.py</code> <pre><code>def opi_available() -&gt; bool:\n    return importlib.util.find_spec(\"opi\") is not None\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Opi orca tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/opi_orca_tools.html#cspilot.tools.opi_orca_tools.orca_frequency","level":2,"title":"orca_frequency","text":"<pre><code>orca_frequency(xyz_path: Path | str, workdir: Path | str, method: str, basis: str, charge: int = 0, mult: int = 1, nprocs: int = 1, *, orca_command: str | None = None) -&gt; dict[str, Any]\n</code></pre> Source code in <code>cspilot/tools/opi_orca_tools.py</code> <pre><code>def orca_frequency(\n    xyz_path: Path | str,\n    workdir: Path | str,\n    method: str,\n    basis: str,\n    charge: int = 0,\n    mult: int = 1,\n    nprocs: int = 1,\n    *,\n    orca_command: str | None = None,\n) -&gt; dict[str, Any]:\n    return _run_orca_task(\n        xyz_path=xyz_path,\n        workdir=workdir,\n        method=method,\n        basis=basis,\n        charge=charge,\n        mult=mult,\n        nprocs=nprocs,\n        task=TASK_FREQ,\n        orca_command=orca_command,\n    )\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Opi orca tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/opi_orca_tools.html#cspilot.tools.opi_orca_tools.orca_optimize","level":2,"title":"orca_optimize","text":"<pre><code>orca_optimize(xyz_path: Path | str, workdir: Path | str, method: str, basis: str, charge: int = 0, mult: int = 1, nprocs: int = 1, *, orca_command: str | None = None) -&gt; dict[str, Any]\n</code></pre> Source code in <code>cspilot/tools/opi_orca_tools.py</code> <pre><code>def orca_optimize(\n    xyz_path: Path | str,\n    workdir: Path | str,\n    method: str,\n    basis: str,\n    charge: int = 0,\n    mult: int = 1,\n    nprocs: int = 1,\n    *,\n    orca_command: str | None = None,\n) -&gt; dict[str, Any]:\n    return _run_orca_task(\n        xyz_path=xyz_path,\n        workdir=workdir,\n        method=method,\n        basis=basis,\n        charge=charge,\n        mult=mult,\n        nprocs=nprocs,\n        task=TASK_OPT,\n        orca_command=orca_command,\n    )\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Opi orca tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/opi_orca_tools.html#cspilot.tools.opi_orca_tools.orca_single_point","level":2,"title":"orca_single_point","text":"<pre><code>orca_single_point(xyz_path: Path | str, workdir: Path | str, method: str, basis: str, charge: int = 0, mult: int = 1, nprocs: int = 1, *, orca_command: str | None = None) -&gt; dict[str, Any]\n</code></pre> Source code in <code>cspilot/tools/opi_orca_tools.py</code> <pre><code>def orca_single_point(\n    xyz_path: Path | str,\n    workdir: Path | str,\n    method: str,\n    basis: str,\n    charge: int = 0,\n    mult: int = 1,\n    nprocs: int = 1,\n    *,\n    orca_command: str | None = None,\n) -&gt; dict[str, Any]:\n    return _run_orca_task(\n        xyz_path=xyz_path,\n        workdir=workdir,\n        method=method,\n        basis=basis,\n        charge=charge,\n        mult=mult,\n        nprocs=nprocs,\n        task=TASK_SP,\n        orca_command=orca_command,\n    )\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Opi orca tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/opi_orca_tools.html#cspilot.tools.opi_orca_tools.parse_orca_result","level":2,"title":"parse_orca_result","text":"<pre><code>parse_orca_result(output_path: Path | str) -&gt; dict[str, Any]\n</code></pre> Source code in <code>cspilot/tools/opi_orca_tools.py</code> <pre><code>def parse_orca_result(output_path: Path | str) -&gt; dict[str, Any]:\n    output_path = Path(output_path)\n    result: dict[str, Any] = {\n        \"output_path\": str(output_path),\n        \"status\": \"missing\" if not output_path.exists() else \"parsed\",\n        \"terminated_normally\": None,\n        \"properties\": {},\n        \"errors\": [],\n    }\n    if not output_path.exists():\n        result[\"errors\"].append(f\"ORCA output file not found: {output_path}\")\n        return result\n\n    opi_result = _parse_with_opi(output_path)\n    result.update(opi_result)\n\n    text_result = _parse_orca_text(output_path)\n    result[\"properties\"] = _merge_missing(result.get(\"properties\", {}), text_result[\"properties\"])\n    if result.get(\"terminated_normally\") is None:\n        result[\"terminated_normally\"] = text_result[\"terminated_normally\"]\n    if text_result.get(\"error_message\") and not result.get(\"error_message\"):\n        result[\"error_message\"] = text_result[\"error_message\"]\n    return _jsonable(result)\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Opi orca tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/opi_orca_tools.html#cspilot.tools.opi_orca_tools.single_point_with_orca","level":2,"title":"single_point_with_orca","text":"<pre><code>single_point_with_orca(input_file: Path, run_dir: Path, settings: Settings, method: str, basis: str, charge: int, mult: int) -&gt; tuple[bool, str, ProcessResult | None, dict[str, Any]]\n</code></pre> Source code in <code>cspilot/tools/opi_orca_tools.py</code> <pre><code>def single_point_with_orca(\n    input_file: Path,\n    run_dir: Path,\n    settings: Settings,\n    method: str,\n    basis: str,\n    charge: int,\n    mult: int,\n) -&gt; tuple[bool, str, ProcessResult | None, dict[str, Any]]:\n    result = orca_single_point(\n        xyz_path=input_file,\n        workdir=run_dir,\n        method=method,\n        basis=basis,\n        charge=charge,\n        mult=mult,\n        orca_command=settings.orca_command,\n    )\n    result[\"orca_command\"] = settings.orca_command\n    ok = result.get(\"status\") == \"ok\"\n    message = (\n        \"ORCA single point completed\"\n        if ok\n        else result.get(\"error_message\", \"ORCA single point failed\")\n    )\n    return ok, str(message), None, result\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Opi orca tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/opi_orca_tools.html#cspilot.tools.opi_orca_tools.write_orca_input","level":2,"title":"write_orca_input","text":"<pre><code>write_orca_input(structure_path: Path, run_dir: Path, method: str, basis: str, charge: int, mult: int, task: str = TASK_SP, nprocs: int = 1) -&gt; Path\n</code></pre> Source code in <code>cspilot/tools/opi_orca_tools.py</code> <pre><code>def write_orca_input(\n    structure_path: Path,\n    run_dir: Path,\n    method: str,\n    basis: str,\n    charge: int,\n    mult: int,\n    task: str = TASK_SP,\n    nprocs: int = 1,\n) -&gt; Path:\n    calc = _build_calculator(\n        xyz_path=structure_path,\n        workdir=run_dir,\n        method=method,\n        basis=basis,\n        charge=charge,\n        mult=mult,\n        nprocs=nprocs,\n        task=task,\n    )\n    calc.write_input()\n    return Path(calc.inpfile)\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Opi orca tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/registry.html","level":1,"title":"Registry","text":"","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Registry"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/registry.html#cspilot.tools.registry.call_tool","level":2,"title":"call_tool","text":"<pre><code>call_tool(tool_name: str, args: dict[str, Any], workdir: str) -&gt; dict[str, Any]\n</code></pre> <p>Call one allowlisted function tool; reject arbitrary tool or shell execution.</p> Source code in <code>cspilot/tools/registry.py</code> <pre><code>def call_tool(tool_name: str, args: dict[str, Any], workdir: str) -&gt; dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Call one allowlisted function tool; reject arbitrary tool or shell execution.\"\"\"\n    if tool_name not in get_allowed_tools():\n        raise ValueError(f\"Unknown or disallowed tool: {tool_name}\")\n    if not isinstance(args, dict):\n        raise ValueError(\"Tool args must be a JSON object.\")\n\n    root = Path(workdir)\n    root.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n    token = set_agent_workdir(root)\n    try:\n        arguments = json.dumps(args)\n        context = ToolContext(\n            context=None,\n            tool_name=tool_name,\n            tool_call_id=f\"executor_{tool_name}\",\n            tool_arguments=arguments,\n        )\n        output = asyncio.run(_TOOLS[tool_name].on_invoke_tool(context, arguments))\n    finally:\n        reset_agent_workdir(token)\n\n    if not isinstance(output, dict):\n        raise ValueError(f\"Tool '{tool_name}' returned an unsupported result type.\")\n    return {\"tool_name\": tool_name, **output}\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Registry"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/registry.html#cspilot.tools.registry.get_allowed_tools","level":2,"title":"get_allowed_tools","text":"<pre><code>get_allowed_tools(profile: str | None = None, user_request: str = '') -&gt; list[str]\n</code></pre> <p>Return tool names permitted for the current or requested profile.</p> Source code in <code>cspilot/tools/registry.py</code> <pre><code>def get_allowed_tools(profile: str | None = None, user_request: str = \"\") -&gt; list[str]:\n    \"\"\"Return tool names permitted for the current or requested profile.\"\"\"\n    if profile is None:\n        active = _active_allowed_tools.get()\n        if active is not None:\n            return [name for name in _TOOLS if name in active]\n        profile = \"chem\"\n    groups = allowed_group_names(profile, user_request)\n    allowed = {tool.name for group in groups for tool in _TOOL_GROUPS.get(group, [])}\n    return [name for name in _TOOLS if name in allowed]\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Registry"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/registry.html#cspilot.tools.registry.reset_allowed_profile","level":2,"title":"reset_allowed_profile","text":"<pre><code>reset_allowed_profile(token: Token[set[str] | None]) -&gt; None\n</code></pre> Source code in <code>cspilot/tools/registry.py</code> <pre><code>def reset_allowed_profile(token: Token[set[str] | None]) -&gt; None:\n    _active_allowed_tools.reset(token)\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Registry"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/registry.html#cspilot.tools.registry.set_allowed_profile","level":2,"title":"set_allowed_profile","text":"<pre><code>set_allowed_profile(profile: str, user_request: str = '') -&gt; Token[set[str] | None]\n</code></pre> Source code in <code>cspilot/tools/registry.py</code> <pre><code>def set_allowed_profile(profile: str, user_request: str = \"\") -&gt; Token[set[str] | None]:\n    return _active_allowed_tools.set(set(get_allowed_tools(profile, user_request)))\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Registry"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/result_tools.html","level":1,"title":"Result tools","text":"","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Result tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/result_tools.html#cspilot.tools.result_tools.PROPERTY_ALIASES","level":2,"title":"PROPERTY_ALIASES  <code>module-attribute</code>","text":"<pre><code>PROPERTY_ALIASES = {'gibbs': ['gibbs_free_energy', 'gibbs_energy', 'final_gibbs_energy', 'G'], 'gibbs free energy': ['gibbs_free_energy', 'gibbs_energy', 'final_gibbs_energy', 'G'], 'free energy': ['gibbs_free_energy', 'gibbs_energy', 'final_gibbs_energy', 'G'], 'enthalpy': ['enthalpy', 'thermal_enthalpy', 'H'], 'electronic energy': ['final_energy', 'final_energy_hartree', 'electronic_energy', 'total_energy', 'energy_hartree'], 'total energy': ['final_energy', 'final_energy_hartree', 'electronic_energy', 'total_energy', 'energy_hartree'], 'final energy': ['final_energy', 'final_energy_hartree', 'electronic_energy', 'total_energy', 'energy_hartree'], 'homo lumo gap': ['homo_lumo_gap', 'homo_lumo_gap_ev', 'gap', 'HOMO_LUMO_gap'], 'gap': ['homo_lumo_gap', 'homo_lumo_gap_ev', 'gap', 'HOMO_LUMO_gap'], 'frequencies': ['frequencies', 'vibrational_frequencies']}\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Result tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/result_tools.html#cspilot.tools.result_tools.RESULT_FILENAMES","level":2,"title":"RESULT_FILENAMES  <code>module-attribute</code>","text":"<pre><code>RESULT_FILENAMES = {'result.json', 'workflow_result.json', 'final_state.json', 'execution_result.json'}\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Result tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/result_tools.html#cspilot.tools.result_tools.find_result_json","level":2,"title":"find_result_json","text":"<pre><code>find_result_json(workdir: str, latest: bool = True) -&gt; dict[str, Any]\n</code></pre> <p>Find supported result JSON files recursively below a working directory.</p> Source code in <code>cspilot/tools/result_tools.py</code> <pre><code>def find_result_json(workdir: str, latest: bool = True) -&gt; dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Find supported result JSON files recursively below a working directory.\"\"\"\n    root = Path(workdir).expanduser()\n    if not root.exists():\n        return {\"success\": False, \"workdir\": str(root), \"error\": \"Workdir not found\"}\n\n    matches = [\n        path\n        for path in root.rglob(\"*.json\")\n        if path.name in RESULT_FILENAMES or fnmatch(path.name, \"step_*_result.json\")\n    ]\n    matches.sort(key=lambda path: (path.stat().st_mtime, str(path)), reverse=True)\n    if not matches:\n        return {\"success\": False, \"workdir\": str(root), \"error\": \"No result JSON files found\"}\n\n    paths = [str(path) for path in matches]\n    result: dict[str, Any] = {\"success\": True, \"workdir\": str(root), \"paths\": paths}\n    if latest:\n        result[\"path\"] = paths[0]\n    return result\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Result tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/result_tools.html#cspilot.tools.result_tools.get_property_from_result","level":2,"title":"get_property_from_result","text":"<pre><code>get_property_from_result(path: str, property_name: str) -&gt; dict[str, Any]\n</code></pre> <p>Look up a named calculated property recursively in result JSON.</p> Source code in <code>cspilot/tools/result_tools.py</code> <pre><code>def get_property_from_result(path: str, property_name: str) -&gt; dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Look up a named calculated property recursively in result JSON.\"\"\"\n    loaded = load_result_json(path)\n    if not loaded[\"success\"]:\n        return {\n            \"success\": False,\n            \"property\": property_name,\n            \"source_file\": str(Path(path).expanduser()),\n            \"error\": loaded[\"error\"],\n        }\n\n    lookup_name = _normalize_key(property_name)\n    aliases = PROPERTY_ALIASES.get(lookup_name, [property_name])\n    expected = {_normalize_key(alias) for alias in aliases}\n    found = _recursive_find(loaded[\"data\"], expected)\n    if found is None:\n        return {\n            \"success\": False,\n            \"property\": property_name,\n            \"source_file\": str(Path(path).expanduser()),\n            \"error\": \"Property not found\",\n        }\n\n    matched_key, value = found\n    return {\n        \"success\": True,\n        \"property\": property_name,\n        \"matched_key\": matched_key,\n        \"value\": value,\n        \"source_file\": str(Path(path).expanduser()),\n    }\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Result tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/result_tools.html#cspilot.tools.result_tools.load_result_json","level":2,"title":"load_result_json","text":"<pre><code>load_result_json(path: str) -&gt; dict[str, Any]\n</code></pre> <p>Load a result JSON file.</p> Source code in <code>cspilot/tools/result_tools.py</code> <pre><code>def load_result_json(path: str) -&gt; dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Load a result JSON file.\"\"\"\n    result_path = Path(path).expanduser()\n    if not result_path.exists():\n        return {\"success\": False, \"path\": str(result_path), \"error\": \"Result file not found\"}\n    try:\n        data = json.loads(result_path.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\"))\n    except (OSError, json.JSONDecodeError) as exc:\n        return {\"success\": False, \"path\": str(result_path), \"error\": f\"Could not load JSON: {exc}\"}\n    return {\"success\": True, \"path\": str(result_path), \"data\": data}\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Result tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/xtb_tools.html","level":1,"title":"Xtb tools","text":"","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Xtb tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/tools/xtb_tools.html#cspilot.tools.xtb_tools.optimize_with_xtb","level":2,"title":"optimize_with_xtb","text":"<pre><code>optimize_with_xtb(input_file: Path, run_dir: Path, settings: Settings, charge: int, uhf: int) -&gt; tuple[bool, str, ProcessResult | None, dict[str, str]]\n</code></pre> Source code in <code>cspilot/tools/xtb_tools.py</code> <pre><code>def optimize_with_xtb(\n    input_file: Path,\n    run_dir: Path,\n    settings: Settings,\n    charge: int,\n    uhf: int,\n) -&gt; tuple[bool, str, ProcessResult | None, dict[str, str]]:\n    if not executable_available(settings.xtb_command):\n        return False, f\"Executable not found: {settings.xtb_command}\", None, {}\n\n    command = [\n        settings.xtb_command,\n        input_file.name,\n        \"--opt\",\n        \"--chrg\",\n        str(charge),\n        \"--uhf\",\n        str(uhf),\n    ]\n    process = run_process(command, cwd=run_dir)\n    outputs = {\n        \"optimized_xyz\": str(run_dir / \"xtbopt.xyz\"),\n        \"log\": str(run_dir / \"xtbopt.log\"),\n    }\n    ok = process.returncode == 0\n    message = \"xTB optimization completed\" if ok else \"xTB optimization failed\"\n    return ok, message, process, outputs\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","tools","Xtb tools"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/utils/runner.html","level":1,"title":"Runner","text":"","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","utils","Runner"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/utils/runner.html#cspilot.utils.runner.copy_input","level":2,"title":"copy_input","text":"<pre><code>copy_input(input_path: Path, run_dir: Path, name: str = 'input.xyz') -&gt; Path\n</code></pre> Source code in <code>cspilot/utils/runner.py</code> <pre><code>def copy_input(input_path: Path, run_dir: Path, name: str = \"input.xyz\") -&gt; Path:\n    target = run_dir / name\n    shutil.copy2(input_path, target)\n    return target\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","utils","Runner"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/utils/runner.html#cspilot.utils.runner.executable_available","level":2,"title":"executable_available","text":"<pre><code>executable_available(command: str) -&gt; bool\n</code></pre> Source code in <code>cspilot/utils/runner.py</code> <pre><code>def executable_available(command: str) -&gt; bool:\n    return shutil.which(command) is not None\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","utils","Runner"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/utils/runner.html#cspilot.utils.runner.make_run_dir","level":2,"title":"make_run_dir","text":"<pre><code>make_run_dir(base_dir: Path, command_name: str) -&gt; Path\n</code></pre> Source code in <code>cspilot/utils/runner.py</code> <pre><code>def make_run_dir(base_dir: Path, command_name: str) -&gt; Path:\n    timestamp = datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y%m%d-%H%M%S-%f\")\n    run_dir = base_dir / f\"{timestamp}-{command_name}\"\n    run_dir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=False)\n    return run_dir\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","utils","Runner"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/utils/runner.html#cspilot.utils.runner.run_process","level":2,"title":"run_process","text":"<pre><code>run_process(command: list[str], cwd: Path) -&gt; ProcessResult\n</code></pre> Source code in <code>cspilot/utils/runner.py</code> <pre><code>def run_process(command: list[str], cwd: Path) -&gt; ProcessResult:\n    completed = subprocess.run(\n        command,\n        cwd=cwd,\n        check=False,\n        capture_output=True,\n        text=True,\n    )\n    return ProcessResult(\n        command=command,\n        returncode=completed.returncode,\n        stdout=completed.stdout,\n        stderr=completed.stderr,\n    )\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","utils","Runner"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/utils/runner.html#cspilot.utils.runner.write_json","level":2,"title":"write_json","text":"<pre><code>write_json(path: Path, payload: CommandResult | dict[str, Any]) -&gt; None\n</code></pre> Source code in <code>cspilot/utils/runner.py</code> <pre><code>def write_json(path: Path, payload: CommandResult | dict[str, Any]) -&gt; None:\n    data = payload.model_dump(mode=\"json\") if isinstance(payload, CommandResult) else payload\n    path.write_text(json.dumps(data, indent=2) + \"\\n\", encoding=\"utf-8\")\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","utils","Runner"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/workflows/_common.html","level":1,"title":" common","text":"","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","workflows"," common"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/workflows/_common.html#cspilot.workflows._common.base_workflow_result","level":2,"title":"base_workflow_result","text":"<pre><code>base_workflow_result(workflow: str, input_xyz: Path | str, workdir: Path) -&gt; dict[str, Any]\n</code></pre> Source code in <code>cspilot/workflows/_common.py</code> <pre><code>def base_workflow_result(workflow: str, input_xyz: Path | str, workdir: Path) -&gt; dict[str, Any]:\n    return {\n        \"workflow\": workflow,\n        \"status\": \"failed\",\n        \"input_xyz\": str(Path(input_xyz).resolve()),\n        \"workdir\": str(workdir),\n        \"created_at\": datetime.now().isoformat(),\n        \"steps\": {},\n        \"final_energy_hartree\": None,\n    }\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","workflows"," common"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/workflows/_common.html#cspilot.workflows._common.copy_workflow_input","level":2,"title":"copy_workflow_input","text":"<pre><code>copy_workflow_input(input_xyz: Path | str, workdir: Path) -&gt; Path\n</code></pre> Source code in <code>cspilot/workflows/_common.py</code> <pre><code>def copy_workflow_input(input_xyz: Path | str, workdir: Path) -&gt; Path:\n    input_xyz = Path(input_xyz).resolve()\n    target = workdir / \"input.xyz\"\n    shutil.copy2(input_xyz, target)\n    return target\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","workflows"," common"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/workflows/_common.html#cspilot.workflows._common.extract_final_energy","level":2,"title":"extract_final_energy","text":"<pre><code>extract_final_energy(orca_result: dict[str, Any]) -&gt; float | None\n</code></pre> Source code in <code>cspilot/workflows/_common.py</code> <pre><code>def extract_final_energy(orca_result: dict[str, Any]) -&gt; float | None:\n    properties = orca_result.get(\"result\", {}).get(\"properties\", {})\n    energy = properties.get(\"final_energy_hartree\")\n    return float(energy) if energy is not None else None\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","workflows"," common"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/workflows/_common.html#cspilot.workflows._common.init_workflow_run","level":2,"title":"init_workflow_run","text":"<pre><code>init_workflow_run(workflow_name: str, settings: Settings | None = None) -&gt; tuple[Settings, Path]\n</code></pre> Source code in <code>cspilot/workflows/_common.py</code> <pre><code>def init_workflow_run(workflow_name: str, settings: Settings | None = None) -&gt; tuple[Settings, Path]:\n    settings = settings or load_settings()\n    return settings, make_run_dir(settings.runs_dir, workflow_name)\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","workflows"," common"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/workflows/_common.html#cspilot.workflows._common.optimizer_failed","level":2,"title":"optimizer_failed","text":"<pre><code>optimizer_failed(result: dict[str, Any], step_name: str, message: str) -&gt; dict[str, Any]\n</code></pre> Source code in <code>cspilot/workflows/_common.py</code> <pre><code>def optimizer_failed(result: dict[str, Any], step_name: str, message: str) -&gt; dict[str, Any]:\n    result[\"status\"] = \"skipped\"\n    result[\"message\"] = message\n    result[\"failed_step\"] = step_name\n    return result\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","workflows"," common"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/workflows/_common.html#cspilot.workflows._common.write_workflow_result","level":2,"title":"write_workflow_result","text":"<pre><code>write_workflow_result(workdir: Path, result: dict[str, Any]) -&gt; Path\n</code></pre> Source code in <code>cspilot/workflows/_common.py</code> <pre><code>def write_workflow_result(workdir: Path, result: dict[str, Any]) -&gt; Path:\n    result_path = workdir / \"workflow_result.json\"\n    result[\"workflow_result_path\"] = str(result_path)\n    result_path.write_text(json.dumps(result, indent=2) + \"\\n\", encoding=\"utf-8\")\n    return result_path\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","workflows"," common"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/workflows/mace_to_orca.html","level":1,"title":"Mace to orca","text":"","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","workflows","Mace to orca"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/workflows/mace_to_orca.html#cspilot.workflows.mace_to_orca.run_mace_to_orca","level":2,"title":"run_mace_to_orca","text":"<pre><code>run_mace_to_orca(input_xyz: Path | str, charge: int = 0, mult: int = 1, method: str = 'r2scan-3c', basis: str = 'def2-SVP', model: Path | str | None = None, fmax: float = 0.05, steps: int = 200, nprocs: int = 1, settings: Settings | None = None) -&gt; dict[str, Any]\n</code></pre> Source code in <code>cspilot/workflows/mace_to_orca.py</code> <pre><code>def run_mace_to_orca(\n    input_xyz: Path | str,\n    charge: int = 0,\n    mult: int = 1,\n    method: str = \"r2scan-3c\",\n    basis: str = \"def2-SVP\",\n    model: Path | str | None = None,\n    fmax: float = 0.05,\n    steps: int = 200,\n    nprocs: int = 1,\n    settings: Settings | None = None,\n) -&gt; dict[str, Any]:\n    settings, workdir = init_workflow_run(\"mace-orca\", settings)\n    result = base_workflow_result(\"mace-orca\", input_xyz, workdir)\n\n    input_copy = copy_workflow_input(input_xyz, workdir)\n    model_path = Path(model or os.getenv(\"MACE_MODEL\", \"model_path\")).expanduser()\n    mace_dir = workdir / \"01_mace_opt\"\n    mace_dir.mkdir()\n    mace_input = copy_workflow_input(input_copy, mace_dir)\n    mace_ok, mace_message, mace_outputs = optimize_with_mace(\n        mace_input,\n        mace_dir,\n        model_path,\n        fmax=fmax,\n        steps=steps,\n    )\n    result[\"steps\"][\"mace_opt\"] = {\n        \"status\": \"ok\" if mace_ok else \"skipped\",\n        \"message\": mace_message,\n        \"model\": str(model_path),\n        \"outputs\": mace_outputs,\n    }\n\n    optimized_xyz = Path(mace_outputs.get(\"optimized_xyz\", mace_dir / \"mace_opt.xyz\"))\n    if not mace_ok or not optimized_xyz.exists():\n        optimizer_failed(result, \"mace_opt\", mace_message)\n        write_workflow_result(workdir, result)\n        return result\n\n    orca_dir = workdir / \"02_orca_sp\"\n    orca_result = orca_single_point(\n        optimized_xyz,\n        orca_dir,\n        method,\n        basis,\n        charge=charge,\n        mult=mult,\n        nprocs=nprocs,\n        orca_command=settings.orca_command,\n    )\n    result[\"steps\"][\"orca_sp\"] = orca_result\n    result[\"final_energy_hartree\"] = extract_final_energy(orca_result)\n    result[\"status\"] = \"ok\" if orca_result.get(\"status\") == \"ok\" else \"failed\"\n    if result[\"status\"] != \"ok\":\n        result[\"message\"] = orca_result.get(\"error_message\", \"ORCA single point failed\")\n\n    write_workflow_result(workdir, result)\n    return result\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","workflows","Mace to orca"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/workflows/xtb_to_orca_freq.html","level":1,"title":"Xtb to orca freq","text":"","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","workflows","Xtb to orca freq"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/workflows/xtb_to_orca_freq.html#cspilot.workflows.xtb_to_orca_freq.run_xtb_to_orca_freq","level":2,"title":"run_xtb_to_orca_freq","text":"<pre><code>run_xtb_to_orca_freq(input_xyz: Path | str, charge: int = 0, mult: int = 1, method: str = 'r2scan-3c', basis: str = 'def2-SVP', uhf: int = 0, nprocs: int = 1, settings: Settings | None = None) -&gt; dict[str, Any]\n</code></pre> Source code in <code>cspilot/workflows/xtb_to_orca_freq.py</code> <pre><code>def run_xtb_to_orca_freq(\n    input_xyz: Path | str,\n    charge: int = 0,\n    mult: int = 1,\n    method: str = \"r2scan-3c\",\n    basis: str = \"def2-SVP\",\n    uhf: int = 0,\n    nprocs: int = 1,\n    settings: Settings | None = None,\n) -&gt; dict[str, Any]:\n    settings, workdir = init_workflow_run(\"xtb-orca-freq\", settings)\n    result = base_workflow_result(\"xtb-orca-freq\", input_xyz, workdir)\n\n    input_copy = copy_workflow_input(input_xyz, workdir)\n    xtb_dir = workdir / \"01_xtb_opt\"\n    xtb_dir.mkdir()\n    xtb_input = copy_workflow_input(input_copy, xtb_dir)\n    xtb_ok, xtb_message, xtb_process, xtb_outputs = optimize_with_xtb(\n        xtb_input,\n        xtb_dir,\n        settings,\n        charge,\n        uhf,\n    )\n    result[\"steps\"][\"xtb_opt\"] = {\n        \"status\": \"ok\" if xtb_ok else (\"failed\" if xtb_process is not None else \"skipped\"),\n        \"message\": xtb_message,\n        \"outputs\": xtb_outputs,\n        \"process\": xtb_process.model_dump(mode=\"json\") if xtb_process is not None else None,\n    }\n\n    optimized_xyz = Path(xtb_outputs.get(\"optimized_xyz\", xtb_dir / \"xtbopt.xyz\"))\n    if not xtb_ok or not optimized_xyz.exists():\n        optimizer_failed(result, \"xtb_opt\", xtb_message)\n        write_workflow_result(workdir, result)\n        return result\n\n    orca_dir = workdir / \"02_orca_freq\"\n    orca_result = orca_frequency(\n        optimized_xyz,\n        orca_dir,\n        method,\n        basis,\n        charge=charge,\n        mult=mult,\n        nprocs=nprocs,\n        orca_command=settings.orca_command,\n    )\n    result[\"steps\"][\"orca_freq\"] = orca_result\n    result[\"final_energy_hartree\"] = extract_final_energy(orca_result)\n    result[\"status\"] = \"ok\" if orca_result.get(\"status\") == \"ok\" else \"failed\"\n    if result[\"status\"] != \"ok\":\n        result[\"message\"] = orca_result.get(\"error_message\", \"ORCA frequency failed\")\n\n    write_workflow_result(workdir, result)\n    return result\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","workflows","Xtb to orca freq"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/workflows/xtb_to_orca_sp.html","level":1,"title":"Xtb to orca sp","text":"","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","workflows","Xtb to orca sp"],"tags":[]},{"location":"reference/cspilot/workflows/xtb_to_orca_sp.html#cspilot.workflows.xtb_to_orca_sp.run_xtb_to_orca_sp","level":2,"title":"run_xtb_to_orca_sp","text":"<pre><code>run_xtb_to_orca_sp(input_xyz: Path | str, charge: int = 0, mult: int = 1, method: str = 'r2scan-3c', basis: str = 'def2-SVP', uhf: int = 0, nprocs: int = 1, settings: Settings | None = None) -&gt; dict[str, Any]\n</code></pre> Source code in <code>cspilot/workflows/xtb_to_orca_sp.py</code> <pre><code>def run_xtb_to_orca_sp(\n    input_xyz: Path | str,\n    charge: int = 0,\n    mult: int = 1,\n    method: str = \"r2scan-3c\",\n    basis: str = \"def2-SVP\",\n    uhf: int = 0,\n    nprocs: int = 1,\n    settings: Settings | None = None,\n) -&gt; dict[str, Any]:\n    settings, workdir = init_workflow_run(\"xtb-orca-sp\", settings)\n    result = base_workflow_result(\"xtb-orca-sp\", input_xyz, workdir)\n\n    input_copy = copy_workflow_input(input_xyz, workdir)\n    xtb_dir = workdir / \"01_xtb_opt\"\n    xtb_dir.mkdir()\n    xtb_input = copy_workflow_input(input_copy, xtb_dir)\n    xtb_ok, xtb_message, xtb_process, xtb_outputs = optimize_with_xtb(\n        xtb_input,\n        xtb_dir,\n        settings,\n        charge,\n        uhf,\n    )\n    result[\"steps\"][\"xtb_opt\"] = {\n        \"status\": \"ok\" if xtb_ok else (\"failed\" if xtb_process is not None else \"skipped\"),\n        \"message\": xtb_message,\n        \"outputs\": xtb_outputs,\n        \"process\": xtb_process.model_dump(mode=\"json\") if xtb_process is not None else None,\n    }\n\n    optimized_xyz = Path(xtb_outputs.get(\"optimized_xyz\", xtb_dir / \"xtbopt.xyz\"))\n    if not xtb_ok or not optimized_xyz.exists():\n        optimizer_failed(result, \"xtb_opt\", xtb_message)\n        write_workflow_result(workdir, result)\n        return result\n\n    orca_dir = workdir / \"02_orca_sp\"\n    orca_result = orca_single_point(\n        optimized_xyz,\n        orca_dir,\n        method,\n        basis,\n        charge=charge,\n        mult=mult,\n        nprocs=nprocs,\n        orca_command=settings.orca_command,\n    )\n    result[\"steps\"][\"orca_sp\"] = orca_result\n    result[\"final_energy_hartree\"] = extract_final_energy(orca_result)\n    result[\"status\"] = \"ok\" if orca_result.get(\"status\") == \"ok\" else \"failed\"\n    if result[\"status\"] != \"ok\":\n        result[\"message\"] = orca_result.get(\"error_message\", \"ORCA single point failed\")\n\n    write_workflow_result(workdir, result)\n    return result\n</code></pre>","path":["Code Documentation","cspilot","workflows","Xtb to orca sp"],"tags":[]}]};